title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; set aside to cool.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk and eggs.
Stir in vanilla and vinegar.
Add butter and nuts.
Put in crust and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: crispy baked onion rings(low-fat)
directions: Cut each onion into 4 thick slices; separate into rings (reserve small rings for another use).
Set aside.
Combine cereal and next 3 ingredients; divide in half and set aside.
Beat egg substitute at high speed with an electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Dip half of onion rings in egg substitute; dredge in half of crumb mixture.
Place in a single layer on baking sheets coated with cooking spray.
Repeat procedure with remaining onion rings, egg substitute and crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, or until crisp.
Serve warm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water until they pop open.
Pour in sugar, marshmallows and cherry jello.
Stir until jello and sugar are dissolved.
Refrigerate until mixture starts to set.
Add the celery, apples and pecans.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: cousin agnes' bread pudding
directions: Put sugar on bottom of double boiler insert.
Add bread.
Mix eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Place insert over hot water.
Cook until set 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove insert and let cool.
When cool, place plate over top of pan and invert pudding. Serve warm or cold.

title: mostaccioli with bacon and mushrooms
directions: In a medium skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove from fat and set aside.
Add mushrooms to bacon fat. Cook until golden; drain and set aside.
Prepare mostaccioli according to package directions. Drain.
In same saucepan, combine half and half, butter, parsley flakes, salt, garlic and hot pepper sauce.
Heat just until butter melts, stirring frequently. Combine bacon, mushrooms, hot mostaccioli, half and half mixture and Parmesan cheese. Toss to coat.
Place on warm serving platter. Garnish with green onions.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf with tangy sauce
directions: Mix all together well and spread into loaf pan.
Spread tangy sauce over meat loaf and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: bohemian pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in quart jars.
Add garlic, dill weed and peppers.
Mix all other ingredients.
Fill jars with liquid. Store in cool dark place for 2 weeks.

title: candied kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa into 1/2-inch pieces. Cook in microwave for 5 minutes or until fully cooked. Mix all other ingredients together. Pour mixture over cooked kielbasa and mix together. Heat in microwave 5 more minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Stir in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared crust. Sprinkle with chopped peanuts, if desired.
Freeze until firm and serve.
For storage longer than 4 to 6 hours, wrap the pie well for freezing to prevent dehydration.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage.
Drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard. Line 13 x 9-inch baking dish with bread.
Top with sausage, then cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until shortening is the size of peas.
Add buttermilk and stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a heavily floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.

title: cool cake
directions: Bake cake as directed for about 25 to 30 minutes in a rectangular pan.
Then remove from oven and punch holes all through the cake with a fork.
Then pour the condensed milk on the cake, covering it completely.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Then mix the rest of the ingredients together and spread over the cake and store in refrigerator.

title: spam salad
directions: Cube Spam into 1/2 to 3/4-inch cubes.
Put into a pan.
Add cooled, cubed potatoes.
Add salt and pepper as desired.
Add chopped onion.
Mix well with sour cream.
Before serving, add croutons (do not refrigerate with croutons, they will get mushy). Serve directly on plate or on lettuce leaf as garnish.

title: microwave rice
directions: Use 1 part rice to 2 parts water.
Wash rice and drain.
Add water and salt.
Cover microwave dish or Pyrex dish with paper towel.
Place in microwave and cook on High for 18 minutes.
Let set for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: hominy bake
directions: Combine soup, peppers, celery seed, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Place over medium heat until mixture is heated thoroughly. Place hominy in greased baking dish; pour soup mixture over hominy; top with crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Yields: 12 servings.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Cream butter and cheese together.
Mix in all spices.
Serve at room temperature.
Can be frozen.

title: love feast pumpkin bread(makes 4 loaves)
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin and eggs in large bowl.
Blend well. Add oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Grease baking pans well. Bake at 350°.

title: two cheese fettuccine primavera
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in medium saucepan.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Toss hot pasta with sauce and remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onions; add seasonings.
Dip each tortilla in warm oil.
On each one, spoon 2 tablespoons sauce, a generous tablespoon of filling and a sprinkling of cheese; roll up and place together in large pan.
Pour remaining sauce and cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: meatless spaghetti sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan under medium heat, saute onion, garlic and crushed red pepper in margarine and olive oil until tender. Add basil, oregano and thyme.
Pour in stewed tomatoes, roughly chopping up the individual tomatoes to desired consistency.
Add tomato paste and mix thoroughly.
Mix in the honey and turn down heat to low.
Simmer, stirring frequently, for about 20 minutes. Serve with pasta of choice.

title: salmon salad
directions: Combine salmon, sour cream, artichokes, green onion, dill, Tabasco sauce, mustard and lemon juice in a blender.
Process until firmly chopped.
Add remaining ingredients.
Process for 1/2 minute.
Cover and refrigerate overnight before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: duffy's poppy seed cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Stir together the poppy seed and buttermilk; cover and refrigerate overnight. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Beat in vanilla and grated orange rind.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with poppy seed mixture, mixing until just smooth each time.
Turn half the batter in prepared pan; sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon mixture; add remaining batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Place cake on wire rack to cool 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan to cool completely.
The cake becomes moist when stored in a tightly covered container for several days.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Blend ingredients together and add asparagus pieces last. Mix and pour into casserole dish.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together and refrigerate. Form into walnut size balls and roll in sugar. Place on cookie sheet and press out with the bottom of a glass. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seasons green beans
directions: Cook beans as directed, then add all ingredients until done. Cook bacon; crumble on top of beans.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add salt and pepper.
Add vegetables in layers without mixing.
Last, sprinkle rice on top (do not stir). Simmer until done (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Mix before serving. Serves 6.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices using wire whisk; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and nuts, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: italian eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant and onions in water to cover 20 minutes.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Place in greased casserole and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown. Serves 6.

title: veal piccata
directions: With meat mallet, pound cutlets to 1/8-inch thickness.
On waxed paper, sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
Add flour and coat cutlets.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot olive oil and butter, cook veal a few pieces at a time until lightly browned on both sides.
Add more olive oil if necessary.
Reduce heat to low.
Into drippings in skillet, stir water, wine, bouillon and 1/2 teaspoon of salt, scraping to loosen brown bits.
Return veal to skillet; cover and simmer 15 minutes until cutlets are tender.
Cut 1 lemon and squeeze out juice.
Thinly slice the other.
Remove cutlets to platter; keep warm.
Stir lemon juice in pan.
Heat until boiling over high heat.
Spoon over cutlets.
Garnish with parsley. Serves 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in microwave on High; stir in flour until smooth. Microwave 30 to 45
seconds until heated.
Blend in milk smoothly. Microwave 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes until thickened, stirring every minute.
Stir in cheese until melted, 15 to 20 seconds.
Mix in macaroni well.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Mix soup with milk; stir constantly while heating.
Don't boil.
Add broccoli, pepper to taste, butter and herb.
Heat to bubbly and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into greased casserole dish and bake 35-45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: sweet chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix flour with sugar, salt, cream of tartar, soda and cinnamon.
Cream butter until softened.
Add flour mixture, milk and vanilla. Mix until all flour is moistened; then beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally. Add eggs and chocolate.
Beat 1 minute longer.

title: hot crabmeat spread
directions: Combine crab, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, curry powder, Worcestershire sauce and onion to taste.
Put in 7 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; top with cheese and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and cream cheese.
Blend well.
Put in pie crust and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool and add pie filling.
Top with whipped cream.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Note recipe calls for less milk than package does.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line dish with graham crackers. Cover with pudding mix. Finish with crackers on top.

title: apple crisp pudding
directions: Butter casserole dish, add apples and pour water mixed with cinnamon over them.
Mix together sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Spread mixture over apples and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add milk and corn.
Mix again.
Pour into a casserole baking dish about 2 inches deep.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: out-of-this-world rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
In large bowl, combine shortening, sugar, beaten eggs, 1 cup warm
water and salt.
Stir in softened yeast and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth and blended.
Add remaining flour to make a soft dough and mix well. Cover and allow to rise
in a warm place until double in bulk. This takes about 1 hour.
Punch down and place in refrigerator overnight.
Divide dough in half and roll each portion into a rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with softened butter.
Roll each rectangle jelly roll style and cut into 1-inch slices.
Place cut side down in greased muffin tins.
Cover and let rise 2 hours. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen large rolls.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, dry milk, salt and sugar. Add pecans; mix well.
Combine beaten eggs, butter, bananas and lemon juice.
Add dry ingredients; mix only until flour is moistened.
Divide into 6 well-greased loaf pans (3 1/2 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch).
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until done.
Cool thoroughly.
Wrap in foil; store overnight.
Good for freezing.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag, mix all ingredients except parsley.
Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes in shallow pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Mix and pour into pastry.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: meringue(that doesn't weep)
directions: Combine in a small saucepan, dry ingredients and water over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and clear.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form by gradually adding 4 tablespoons sugar, beating well.
Slowly add cooled cooked cornstarch mixture, beating until stiff glossy peaks form.
Spread meringue evenly to edge of pie crust to seal all around.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden.

title: carrots supreme
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of water until just barely tender; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: cucumber appetizers
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, cream cheese and Good Seasons mix. Spread on slices of cocktail rye bread.
Top with a thin slice of cucumber. Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Boil hamburger meat, potatoes and onion in water until tender. Add Spanish rice, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook for 20 minutes over medium heat.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil in saucepan margarine, shortening, cocoa and water.
Remove from heat; add dry ingredients, then add buttermilk, vanilla, baking soda and eggs. Beat and pour into greased and floured large cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
During last 5 minutes of baking time, make frosting as follows.

title: ham and cheesy potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and cube cheese. Mix soup and milk until creamy. Layer potatoes, cheese, ham and onion in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Pour half the soup over and repeat the layers. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: banana brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt chips with butter.
In a large mixer bowl, beat chocolate mixture with milk, biscuit mix, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in walnuts.
Place bananas on bottom of pastry shell. Pour chocolate mixture over bananas.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring beets to a slow boil; cook until tender and skins peel off easily.
At this stage, you just boil the beets in water and then discard this water.
Boil remaining ingredients together and add beets.
Bring back to a boil.
Pack and seal in jars.

title: peaches n' cheese cream pie
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients 2 minutes. Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan. Drain the peaches and save juice.
Lay peaches on top of batter. Beat the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice for 2 minutes.
Spoon on top of peaches.
Leave a 1-inch margin. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: wild strawberry preserves
directions: To a quart of strawberries, add sugar and water.
Boil slowly for 15 minutes.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, bring to a boil and pour into jars while hot.

title: banana pepper pie
directions: Line an 8 x 8-inch pan with sliced banana peppers. (May use other peppers.)
In a large bowl combine eggs, corn and cheese. Mix well.
Pour over peppers in pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients well and set aside.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Gradually add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Add prunes, vanilla and walnuts. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Glaze while hot.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove caps from mushrooms and chop the stems.
Cut up bacon and fry with mushroom stems.
Add onion, pepper and bread crumbs. Stuff mushroom caps with first mixture.
Place in buttered shallow baking dish.
Salt, cover and refrigerate.
Before baking, sprinkle with the Parmesan and basil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: longhorn baked eggs
directions: Grease 6 custard cups or other microwave-safe dishes; set aside.
Place equal amounts of bacon and cheese in each cup.
Break 1 egg into each cup.
In small bowl, mix sour cream, milk and hot sauce until well blended.
Spoon 3 tablespoons sour cream mixture around each egg.
Gently break egg yolks with fork.
Place egg cups in microwave and cover with paper towel.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on Medium power until eggs are set as desired.
Garnish with chopped green onions or diced tomatoes.

title: larry's hot sausage
directions: Cut sausage into bun sized pieces.
Cook for 15 minutes; drain.
Slice onions and peppers into 1/2-inch strips.
Mix whole tomatoes, Sweet 'N Low and tomato sauce with 1 1/2 cans of water. Cook for 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook another 15 minutes. Add sausage and cook another 15 minutes.
Serve with (soft) sausage buns.
Makes about 20 sandwiches.

title: rotini casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Prepare rotini noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: jello popsicles
directions: Mix, pour into molds and freeze.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and garlic. Stir frequently until meat is no longer pink (do not brown).
Drain fat off. Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 2 to 3 hours until sauce thickens. Spoon over hot dogs. Top with chopped onions, if desired.

title: trifle
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Let set until thick.
Slice cake very thin.
In an attractive bowl, layer the following:

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Put all these ingredients in a bowl and stir together.
Pat dough on sides and bottom of pie pan same as a graham cracker crust.
Bake in 400° oven for about 7 to 10 minutes (not too brown).

title: potato and cabbage casserole
directions: In large pan, heat butter and saute cabbage and onions until wilted.
Place half of the cabbage, onions and potatoes in a 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Put remaining cabbage, potato and onion on top.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in same pan cabbage was cooked in.
Add 1/4 cup flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Add can of broth.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over top of cabbage.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork chops sweet 'n sour
directions: Mix first five ingredients. Melt shortening in skillet. Dredge pork chops in flour mixture and brown in hot fat, slowly.

title: sugar free cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until dry.
Let cool.
Then mix all ingredients well by hand.
Bake in lightly greased bundt pan or 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan for 55 - 60 minutes at 350.

title: my deluxe meatballs
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Make into medium size balls. Place in a casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Cover!
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 375° oven.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add egg and molasses. Add sifted flour, baking soda, salt and ginger.
Roll into balls in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, using electric mixer.
Use apple wedges, orange slices, banana chunks, pineapple chunks, etc. to dip.

title: sausage beef casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Brown beef; drain.
Cook onion and celery in meat fat until tender.
Cook rice and drain.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour, adding cheese to top during last 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb strawberry jam
directions: Mix the rhubarb and sugar together and let set overnight.
In the morning, boil the mixture for 5 minutes, then add the Jell-O. Stir well.
Put in jars to seal.
Very good if you like rhubarb strawberry on your toast.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray muffin pan cups with grease.
In medium bowl, combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and ginger.
In a large bowl with whisk or fork, mix carrots, yogurt, egg substitute, applesauce, raisins, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
With spoon, stir together the 2 mixtures until moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool muffins in pans 10 minutes and remove.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: pork and beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours in a casserole dish, removing cover last 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and shape into small balls.
Cook at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: aunt t's string pie
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper in a large skillet over medium high heat until meat is brown, stirring to separate meat. Drain fat.
Stir in sauces; mix well.
Combine spaghetti, Romano cheese, eggs and butter in large bow; mix well.
Place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread Ricotta cheese over top.
Pour sauce mixture over Ricotta cheese.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top. Bake in pre-heated oven 350° until cheese melts, approximately 20 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Combine sugar, seasoned salt and pepper; place mixture in a shaker.
In a shallow pan, arrange layer of meat strips.
Sprinkle with seasonings and cover with liquid smoke; repeat layers to use all ingredients.
Marinate meat for 8 hours.
Place aluminum foil on oven racks.
Arrange meat strips on foil in single layer.
Set oven temperature at lowest possible setting, leave oven door ajar and bake for 4 to 8 hours or until done to taste.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 4 1/2 x 6 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Mix flour and sugar.
Stir in pecans.
Blend eggs, potatoes, milk and shortening.
Add liquid mixture to flour mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour into pan.
Press pecan halves in top of batter. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: soppin chocolate
directions: Mix and cook sugar, cocoa, flour and milk in saucepan until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour over hot biscuits.

title: susan's salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients except gelatin.
Sprinkle dry gelatin over salad and toss lightly.

title: angel food cake
directions: Break cake and press it in a sheet pan bottom.
Bring juice and Jell-O to a boil, then add can of pineapple, cottage cheese and Dream Whip.
Mix all up in a bowl and pour over cake.
Keep in fridge.
Really good if you are on a diet.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: In heavy skillet or wok, saute onion in oil until transparent, but not browned.
Add rice, water, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper.
Bring to a vigorous boil.
Cover and cook over low heat until all water is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Stir in eggs and green onions.
Cook until eggs are set.
Stir in soy sauce.

title: spiced tea
directions: Use 3 teaspoons per cup and fill with boiling water.

title: granny little's pound cake(in loving memory)
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour (presifted with baking powder) alternately with flavoring.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix until thick; pour into pie shell.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef with onion over medium heat. Drain fat.
In a 3-quart casserole, combine beef mixture with all remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 2 hours or until rice and potatoes are tender.

title: veggies with horseradish cream
directions: In large saucepan fitted with steam basket, bring 1/2 cup water to boil; place vegetables in basket and cook, covered, 4 minutes; remove saucepan from heat.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients except almonds and lettuce leaves.
Put almonds on top.
Serve 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Sweeten this mixture to your taste. Mix cherry Jell-O according to box directions, but use pineapple juice instead of water.
Let jell until syrupy, then add the cranberry relish.
Let set at least 2 hours.
Best when sets overnight.

title: swiss mushroom chicken
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thick. In a shallow bowl, lightly beat the egg. Combine cracker crumbs and salt in another shallow bowl. Dip chicken in egg, then in crumbs. Set aside. In a large ovenproof skillet, saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter until tender. Remove and set aside. In same skillet, melt remaining butter. Add chicken; cook over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes. Top with ham, mushrooms and cheese. Broil until cheese is melted.

title: chinese marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour marinade over vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 2 days before serving.
Drain marinade from vegetables to serve.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Add beef, onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until meat is brown and onion is tender. Stir in catsup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover, simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Blend flour and 1/4 cup water; stir gradually into meat mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Serve over buttered noodles.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: special tea
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store and pack in jars or tin cans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook first three ingredients in a small amount of salted water and drain.
Mix sour cream and soup with vegetables.
Add butter to dressing.
Layer dressing, then squash in buttered casserole dish and finish with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except potatoes. Stir in potatoes.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, uncovered.

title: company shrimp boil
directions: Fill a large pot with water to cover ingredients. Add shrimp and crab boil seasoning.
When water comes to a boil, add sausage and corn. Boil 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and boil 3 minutes.
Drain and serve with butter for the corn and cocktail sauce for the shrimp.
Cole slaw and favorite beverage completes the meal.

title: orange-date-nut cake
directions: Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
While hot, punch many holes with ice pick.
Pour glaze over cake.
Let stand several hours before serving.

title: crunch bars
directions: Bring Karo syrup and white sugar to a boil.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add Special K cereal.
Mix well and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour over Special K mixture.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften the cream cheese and mix with the shredded cheese. Drain the pimentos and chilies and mix in with the above ingredients.
Put in a wreath mold for Christmas and decorate with sliced green olives and a bow.
You can also use chopped walnuts.

title: turnip greens casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together except crumbs and cheese.
Spoon into casserole, cover top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This dish multiplies well for a big crowd.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Pour butter over sugar. Add eggs and vinegar.
Mix well.
Fold in remaining filling ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley flakes, bouillon and seasonings; mix well.
Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender. Gradually add milk to flour, mixing until well blended.
Add milk mixture to vegetables; cook until thickened.
Add Velveeta; stir until melted.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fiesta meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter until tender. Stir in chili sauce.
Combine 1/2 cup this mixture with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Form into a loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve remaining sauce, cold or hot, over meat loaf.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except dressing, Fritos and cheese Add the French dressing. Allow a few hours to marinate in the dressing.
Add cheese and Fritos before serving.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream shortening and butter.
Add sugar and beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add egg yolks and beat until the yolks disappear.
Stir flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan.
May be iced with your favorite chocolate icing.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Take each frank.
Wrap 1/2 slice cheese around it.
Take 1 piece bacon and wrap over the frank and cheese.
Wrap 1 biscuit around frank.
Continue until ingredients are used up.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 450° until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: chewy bars
directions: Heat butter in pan in 350° oven until melted.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over butter.
Press down with fork. Sprinkle chocolate chips and coconut over crumbs.
Drizzle condensed milk evenly over top.
Cover with marshmallows.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Refrigerate for one hour before cutting into bars.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in tightly closed jar. Combine 1 tablespoon of mix and 1 cup of hot water in a mug; add sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 cups of mix.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cherries in a mixing bowl. Blend on low speed of electric mixer 15 seconds; increase to medium speed and blend 30 additional seconds.
Stir in cherries. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan; remove to wire rack and cool completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: hot crab triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat cheese until fluffy.
Combine mustard with milk and add to cheese with salt, cayenne, crab meat, chives, and almonds.
Mix well and spread generously on bread slices.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Cut each slice in 4 triangles; put on a baking sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until well browned.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and mash while hot.
Add butter, beat eggs with half of sugar.
Add to potatoes and butter mixture.
Add milk and rest of sugar.
Mix in spices (should be creamy).
Pour into pie shells, bake in oven at 350° for one hour or until custard is set and a toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: one step pie crust
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
With hands, form dough to fit pie pan.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Cook butter and onion until tender.
Add flour until mixed well.
Add milk, salt and pepper and cook until thickens a little. Add sherry and crab meat.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread sliced apples in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with water, cinnamon and salt.
Work remaining ingredients together until crumbly.
Use pastry blender, fork or fingers.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple dessert cake
directions: Follow directions on box for cake mix. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool. With electric mixer, beat cream cheese, milk and pudding until thick. Spread over cooled cake.
Spread drained pineapple over creamed mixture. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with some chopped nuts and coconut.
Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: round steak
directions: Melt shortening in a skillet.
Cut round steak in sections. Brown until done.
Empty cans of mushroom soup and stir together. Let simmer for about 1 hour.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Prepare ribs.
Remove excess fat, wash and pat dry with paper towel.
Place ribs in baking pan; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover with chopped onions and chopped celery.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Bake slowly in 325° oven until tender (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Drain fat and pour 1/2 bottle or more barbecue sauce over ribs and return to oven for 1/2 hour, baste occasionally and remove from oven.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Combine and mix first 6 ingredients. Spread in 9 x 13 baking pan. Sprinkle 2/3 of spice cake mix on top. Sprinkle on top of cake mix the chopped walnuts. Drizzle butter over top. Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed cake with anise hyssop
directions: Combine and set aside buttermilk, poppy seed, almond extract and anise hyssop flowers.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Alternately add with buttermilk mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour half the batter in a greased tube or bundt pan. Sprinkle half of the sugar-cinnamon mixture on batter and add the remaining batter and the remaining sugar mixture.
Cut through batter with knife for marble effect.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ice cream party punch
directions: Put pineapple juice, sherbet and ice cream in large mixing bowl and mix together.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale. Makes 24 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except margarine. Melt oleo and pour into 9 x 12 casserole dish. Pour mixed ingredients over melted oleo. Do not stir. Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: peach frostee
directions: In a blender, combine canned sliced peaches, dry milk powder, vanilla and cinnamon.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add five ice cubes, one at a time with the motor running.
Blend until smooth. Makes 4 servings.
Calories per serving:
Diabetic exchanges per serving:
milk 1, vegetable 0, fruit 1/2, bread 0, meat 0 and fat 0.

title: bartley's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water until just done and rinse in cold water.
Add enough salad dressing to thoroughly coat the pasta. Add Parmesan cheese and vegetables.
You may use any other vegetable you choose.
Enjoy!
This makes enough for 10.

title: german's sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating after each.
Blend in vanilla and melted chocolate.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add seasoning mix.
Let cool. Mix cream cheese and chip dip together.
Spread creamed mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with meat mixture, lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Cube potatoes and carrots.
Add remaining vegetables.
Simmer in water with salt and chicken bouillon for 20 minutes.
Add cheese, allow to melt.
Add milk and shrimp and Worcestershire. Simmer gently, stirring from bottom frequently.
Do not boil. Thicken with cornstarch and water.
Serve with salad and toasted French bread.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Cook sausage and onion.
Drain grease.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
When set in the middle it is ready to eat.
Can be prepared the night before and cooked in the morning.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in unbaked 9-inch pie shell. In a bowl, add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour over the bacon and cheese mixture.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes; cut into wedges and serve.

title: dot's spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
In another pan place tomato soup and 2 cans of water.
Add chopped green pepper and olive juice.
Boil for a few minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and drain spaghetti or vermicelli.
Put in large container.
Add meat, sauce and cheese to spaghetti.
Mix well.
Put in 2 casseroles (13 x 9-inch). Spread can of undiluted mushroom soup on top of each.
Decorate with sliced olives.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding beans last. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs, butter and milk, then coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top should be crusty and firm.
The center should become more firm as it cools.

title: wonderful meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Add meat, eggs, onions, salt, pepper and soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine brown sugar, catsup, nutmeg and mustard; spread over meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn relish
directions: In a 6 to 8-quart saucepot, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to medium and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Immediately fill hot pint or half pint jars with mixture, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Carefully run a utensil down inside of jar to remove trapped air bubbles.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean.
Place hot lids on jars and screw bands on firmly. Process pints or half-pints in boiling water canner for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 pints or 10 to 12 half pints.

title: poor man's filet mignon
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce. Form into 12 thick patties.

Wrap bacon slice around the sides of each patty and secure with a toothpick. Bake on a rack at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done. Baste frequently with barbecue sauce the last 30 minutes. Serves 12.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour and soda.
Combine butter, sugar and pudding mix in large bowl.
Beat until smooth. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoon about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara*
directions: Mix cream, egg, Parmesan cheese and bacon together.
Toss with cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with salt, Parmesan cheese and plenty of freshly ground black pepper.
Serve immediately!

title: italian chocolate cookies(a very old recipe)
directions: Make enough perked coffee to cover raisins.
Pour over raisins and let cool.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Place unpeeled potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with water.
Cook just until tender, but firm.
Drain and cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Place in an ungreased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Add pimientos, onion, garlic and onion salt; toss gently. Sprinkle with cheese.
Place bread cubes on top and pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until bread is toasted.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix until smooth.
Slice a thin slice off tops of tomatoes and carefully remove insides.
Invert on paper towel to drain.
Fill with cream cheese mixture.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: tutti-frutti
directions: Do not drain fruit.
Mix and chill first 6 ingredients.
Just before serving, add bananas.
Serve plain or with whipped topping.

title: chilled summer squash soup
directions: In a large saucepan, place all the squash.
Add the onion, garlic, broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until the vegetables are very tender.
Allow to cool slightly; puree in a food processor or blender with basil, parsley and lemon juice until smooth.
Place in a container, cover and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, add the buttermilk.
Whisk until smooth and adjust the seasonings with salt and pepper.
Serve chilled and garnished with chopped basil and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: golden cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Moisten potatoes.
Drop in bag and shake well.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange potatoes in one layer.
Bake at 425°.
Turn once.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and store in a tightly covered jar.
Use 1-2 tsp. per cup of hot water.

title: made-in-the-shade pork chops
directions: In shaker jar, combine lemonade concentrate, soy sauce and seasonings.
Shake ingredients vigorously to blend.
Pour half of marinade into shallow pan and add chops in single layer.
Pour remaining marinade over steaks; cover pan and place in refrigerator approximately 24 hours.
Meat should be turned once or twice during refrigeration.
Remove from refrigerator three or four hours before grilling.
Grill over medium coals 40 to 45 minutes.
Baste steaks occasionally with remaining marinade.

title: wilted lettuce salad(microwave)
directions: Cook
bacon
loosely covered with paper towel in microwave oven
for
to 3 1/2 minutes or until crisp.
Reserve 2 tablespoons
of drippings.
Tear lettuce into small pieces and combine
with onion in salad bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Combine
vinegar,
reserved
bacon
drippings,
sugar, water, salt,
mustard and pepper in 1 cup glass measuring cup. Cook uncovered
in
a
microwave for 1 minute or until mixture boils,
stirring
to
dissolve sugar.
Pour over salad greens, tossing
to coat well.
Garnish with crumbled bacon and radish slices.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with whole graham crackers, breaking crackers if necessary.
Prepare pudding as directed on package. Let stand 5 minutes, then blend in whipped topping.
Spread 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers; top with remaining pudding mixture and remaining crackers.
Spread pie filling over top layer of crackers.
Chill 3 hours.
(Best if done a day ahead.)

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Line bottom of bowl with 1/2 cake that has been broken into pieces.
Mix together milk, cream cheese, and sugar.
Mix in Cool Whip and beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture over first layer of cake.
Repeat layers.
Pour pie filling on top.

title: cinnamon pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 325°. In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon soda, cocoa and cinnamon; add alternately with sour cream, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 75 minutes, or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Take off wire rack; cool completely.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Wash squash. Slice in rounds, fairly thin. Salt, pepper and roll in flour.
Have cooking oil medium-hot and fry until crisp and golden brown. Serve while hot.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix together.
Add water until soupy.
Stuff turkey.
Put water in bottom of pan with turkey.
Bake 3 hours; 45 minutes at 400° and the balance at 325°.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Mix together oil, Parmesan cheese, salt, garlic powder, paprika and pepper.
Dip potatoes in mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix and add 1 roll Ritz crackers (crushed) on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: granny's kitchen
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk, then yeast mixture.
Stir until thoroughly moistened.
Turn out onto floured board and knead a minute or two.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet. Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Yield:
60 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Soak dried beans overnight.
Wash thoroughly and put in pot of boiling water.
Add chopped onion and cubed potatoes.
Add seasonings to taste.
Bring to a boil, then cook on low until beans are done and soup is thick.
Mash beans with wooden spoon while in the pot.
Remove hot pepper.
Add olive oil and sherry and simmer another 15 minutes.
If sausage is added, omit olive oil and add sausage along with potatoes and onion, but boil sausage separately first to remove fat.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Set aside in bowl the nuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Cream butter. Add white sugar.
Add the eggs and beat fast.
Measure flour, baking powder and salt.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with sour cream and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Put 1/2 batter in cake pan.
Spread filling over the rest of batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Cool in pan on rack for 1/2 hour.
Freezes nicely.
Thaw covered. Better the older it gets.

title: ed mcmahon's turkey dressing(celebrity recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stuff into neck and body cavities of turkey.
If preferred, bake in separate pan. Enough stuffing for a 16 pound turkey.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly. Cover and chill overnight.
Drain well before serving.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, sour cream, mayonnaise and cheese.
Place in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and mix with melted butter. Spread on vegetable mixture and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown and crumble hamburger meat in large skillet.
Chop up onion and bell pepper.
Add to hamburger meat.
Brown until soft. Add tomatoes and enough water to make gravy.
Add seasonings. Cook on low heat 45 minutes.
Add noodles.
Cook 10 minutes or until noodles are done.
Serve with corn bread and salad.

title: creamy dill dip
directions: Mix together in blender or food processor until smooth.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken, pat dry with paper towels.
Heat oil and butter in 6-quart Dutch oven.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time, and brown well on all sides. Remove as browned.
Return chicken to Dutch oven; add tomato sauce, tomatoes, wine, basil, oregano, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered for 45 to 50 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Combine flour with 3 tablespoons water; stir into sauce.
Add mushrooms; cook 10 minutes longer or until sauce is thickened.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Gradually mix the ingredients, except cracker crumbs and melted margarine, together into a large bowl, then pour into a casserole bowl.
Add the crushed crackers evenly on top, then spread the melted margarine evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly. Use only enough mayonnaise to moisten the mixture.
Chill well about 1 to 5 hours before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Spread crumbs into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Make pudding and pour over crumbs.
Slice bananas over pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip. Layer on strawberries and pineapple.
Sprinkle on coconut.

title: sausage and salsa skillet dinner
directions: Cut sausage in half lengthwise, cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
In 10-inch skillet, combine rice, sausage, tomatoes, water, salsa and beans.
Mix well, breaking tomatoes with large spoon.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat, let stand, covered, about 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: roast fresh ham
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients together except ham.
Remove rind from ham. Score fat with a knife.
Rub mixture over ham. Wrap ham in foil or plastic and refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 425°.
Unwrap ham.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Roast, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Baste with drippings every 30 minutes for about 4 hours or until meat thermometer registers 160° internal temperature.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cut bacon in 1-inch pieces and fry.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon grease.
Blend sugar, onion, flour and seasonings into grease in large frying pan. Gradually add water and vinegar. Boil 1 minute. Add potatoes and bacon. Cook 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: snickers bar dessert
directions: Mix vanilla pudding according to directions on package.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Add 2 chopped Snickers.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
This makes 1 large 9-inch pie or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.

title: egg custard
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix 1 cup plain flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, 1 1/2 cups pecan pieces and 1 stick melted butter.
Press in bottom of 12-inch rectangular Pyrex (or 10-inch round).
Bake for 10 minutes at 375° or until light brown.
Chill or allow to cool completely.

title: hearty chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done and cool.
Debone and chop into bite sized pieces.
Save approximately 3 cups of water boiled in.
Chop celery, carrots, onion and garlic into fine pieces.

title: somen noodle salad
directions: Rinse lettuce.
Drain well.
Tear into small pieces.
Clean and slice mushrooms.
Rinse cucumber, green pepper, onion and tomatoes, sliced.
Combine all ingredients in a salad bowl. Garnish with green onions.

title: squash souffle
directions: Chop squash and onion; cook until tender and drain well.
Mix in all other ingredients and stir in saltines.
Place in buttered casserole and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on each side; drain.
Arrange potatoes in a 9 x 12-inch casserole, lightly coated with nonstick spray.
Mix water, soup and sour cream in small bowl; pour over potatoes. Arrange pork chops on top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: caesar salad(serves 6)
directions: Remove	crusts	from bread and spread butter lightly on each side.
Place
in large skillet over moderate heat.	Add a little of	the
remaining	butter.
Brown	bread on each side, drain on paper
towels
and	cube.
Beat
eggs slightly.
Add olive	oil, lemon juice, Parmesan cheese, mustard, pepper and garlic.	Beat until
blended.
Toss
romaine,
dressing
and croutons.

title: carrot tuna noodle salad
directions: Mix carrots, celery and tuna together.
Add mayonnaise.
Just before serving, add noodles.
Serves about 6.

title: donuts
directions: Cut
small
hole in middle of biscuits.
I use medicine bottle.
Deep fry biscuits and the holes until brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: starlight mint surprise cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
In separate bowl, cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Blend in eggs, water and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Put about 1 tablespoon of dough around each mint.
Place on greased baking sheet, about 3 inches apart.
Top with walnut half.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Mix marinade ingredients together and marinate meat overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (uncovered).

title: mama's fudge
directions: Boil until it forms a ball in cold water, then beat and pour into pan to set.

title: hot! hot! dogs
directions: Mix together and simmer for one hour (covered).
Then add 2 cups of water.
Cook one more hour.
Serve hot.
May be put in containers to freeze, if desired.

title: food, facts and fancy cream of potato-vegetable chicken soup
directions: Dice bacon and place in heavy saucepan.
Cook, but do not brown. Remove extra fat. Add diced onion and diced celery.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add potato, broth and bouillon.
Cook until potato is almost (soft) tender.
Add frozen carrots and peas, celery slices, mushroom slices, diced chicken, milk, chicken broth and herb blend.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Melt butter. Add flour to make gravy. Add milk to thicken. Once thickened, add cheese. Arrange broccoli stems facing in the middle. Pour cheese sauce over the broccoli.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut peeled eggplant into 1-inch cubes and soak in salt water in refrigerator 6 hours.
Drain eggplant.
Place in pan.
Cover with water and simmer until soft.
Soak cornbread in milk.
Saute onions, green pepper and celery in butter until all are tender. Combine cooked eggplant, bread crumbs and sauteed vegetables.
Add eggs, pimento and seasoning.
Thoroughly blend and place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then top with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: summer salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in marshmallows until almost dissolved.
Add cream cheese.
Fold in rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish and refrigerate.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Stir jello, sugar and syrup all together.
Bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat and add the baking soda, stirring to mix. Pour over popcorn stirring so all corn is coated.
Grease hands with butter and form into balls.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix and cook 1 minute for each batch, then stir in oatmeal mixture until thick.
Drop onto wax paper.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: In large bowl, mix Bisquick, cheese and sausage meat; add salt and pepper.
Mix well and roll in small ball.
Place in refrigerator half a day or night.
Cut bacon in three strips and wrap each ball with a strip of bacon.
Lap ends and stick toothpick in to hold in place.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together cinnamon and sugar in a small bowl.
In a medium bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla until blended.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder or salt over sugar mixture.
Stir with wooden spoon to make a stiff dough.
Shape dough into walnut-size balls.
Roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture to coat.
Place balls about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.

title: custard pie
directions: Keep half of egg whites to put in last.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, then to 375° to finish.
For 2 pies.

title: cool veggie pizza or mexican siesta pizza
directions: *For Mexican Siesta, add 2 tablespoons of sour cream and 2 tablespoons of taco mix.
Omit mayo and dill.

title: ben grayson's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions in butter until soft.
Add other ingredients and simmer 15 minutes (preferably 30).
Makes about 2 1/2 cups and will be thick.

title: chinese barbecued spareribs
directions: Place ribs on baking sheet. With sharp knife, cut meat between bones. Crush garlic and blend with other ingredients. Spoon sauce on both sides and into cuts. Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes on each side. Serves 4.

title: meal-in-a-dish
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered pan or casserole dish or Dutch oven.
Cook in 300° oven for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
If it gets too dry, add water to make right consistency.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Bone chicken and chip up meat.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Cook vegetables in margarine until onions are transparent. Mix chicken, spaghetti and vegetables with mushroom soup.
Cook around 40 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add chocolate, vanilla, buttermilk and flour to the egg mixture, beating slowly until smooth.
Add the soda mixture and fold in the egg whites.
Bake in layers or in a long, flat pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage, drain and place in 2-quart lightly greased casserole dish.
Melt cheese in soup, pour over cabbage.
Place corn bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350°
until hot and bubbly or brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Mix with cinnamon and sugar. Arrange in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt oleo and add to remaining dry ingredients.
Spoon over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Keep covered with foil and last 15 minutes, uncover to crisp up the topping.

title: estofado
directions: In 10-inch skillet, brown beef cubes in hot oil.
Stir in wine, undrained tomatoes, onion, green pepper, raisins, apricots, salt, pepper and garlic.
In a cheesecloth bag, combine basil, thyme, tarragon and bay leaf.
Add to meat mixture and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Stir mushrooms and olives into stew. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes more.
Discard herb bag.
Blend cold water with flour; stir into stew.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon nuts
directions: Mix cinnamon into sugar; add cream and mix well.
Cook on medium-low heat, stirring constantly; cook to 240°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until syrup coats nuts.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl with fork, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into a ball. Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic film or foil.
Refrigerate until well chilled, overnight.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix fruit, tapioca and sugar.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and drop by spoonfuls on top of fruit. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: diet refrigerator pickles
directions: Put your sliced cucumbers or any cut up vegetables in mixture. Cover and store in refrigerator.
Eat whenever hungry.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Form patties and coat with seafood breader.
Pan-fry.

title: johnny marzette
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 14 x 9-inch roasting pan.
Sprinkle top with 2 cups grated American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: gloria's fried pie dough
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Add liquid ingredients and refrigerate.
This can be stored several days and used as needed.
For fried pies, I roll out a thin saucer-sized circle of dough.
Fill with desired fruit and fold in half.
Press edges with fork and fry in skillet with a little bit of shortening.
This dough is very easy to work with and tastes great.

title: papaya seed dressing
directions: Put vinegar and dry ingredients in blender with motor running. Add oil in steady stream.
Add onion, then papaya seed and blend until seed looks coarsely ground.
Chill for 1 hour.
Good on fruit or green salads.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Beat in milk and vanilla. Serve very cold, sprinkled with nutmeg.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: cauliflower with cheese
directions: Let cauliflower stand in salted water 20 to 30 minutes and rinse. Cover with water. Add the salt and garlic (if desired). Bring to a boil. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until tests done. Drain and place on serving dish. Top with Cheese Sauce and Buttered Bread Crumbs.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Saute onions, zucchini and garlic in margarine or oil. Prebake 1 pie crust until slightly cooked.
Mix together cheese, eggs, milk and dash of Tabasco sauce.
Add sauteed vegetables to egg mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake at about 350° until set, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top after it is baked.

title: sausage pepper quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grate cheeses; set aside.
Cook sausages and drain.
In a skillet, saute vegetables in the butter until soft.
In a large bowl, combine and whisk half and half, milk, eggs and seasonings.
In pie crusts, layer sausages, vegetable mixture and cheeses, two layers per pie.
Pour milk over layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and paprika.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until brown; let sit 15 minutes before slicing to eat.

title: leota's fudge
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, milk and chocolate.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat until soft ball stage is reached. Add butter and put in cool water until mixture is lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until candy stands alone.
Add pecans and mix and turn into greased dish.

title: raspberry crumb bars
directions: Position rack in the center of the oven and preheat to 375 degrees. Butter a 9 x 9 pan.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Whip together the lemonade and the Eagle Brand milk.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Place in freezer.
Pie is ready to eat when frozen.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Combine all ingredients and put in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in eggs; add bananas and mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Brown onion and garlic in margarine.
Add other ingredients except wieners.
Simmer.
Add wieners and cook 10 minutes.

title: old fashion "peach" cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pie filling, eggs, vanilla and nuts. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, butter and flavoring (will be crumbly).
Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine
first	4 ingredients.	Mix sugar and remaining ingredients.
Bring
to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Pour
vinegar
mixture
over vegetables and toss. Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix all together. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: steak marinade
directions: Blend in blender.
Marinate meat overnight, then barbecue. Also good for chicken.

title: slow cooker chicken
directions: Before you go to church Sunday morning, cut up and remove the skin from fryer; salt and flour lightly.
Arrange in single layer in slow cooker.
Slice onion; spread over chicken.
Sprinkle over this the seasoning, thyme and celery
and parsley flakes.
Place lid on cooker; turn on.
Come home from church and eat!

title: summer punch
directions: In a large pitcher or punch bowl, combine all except sherbet. Stir until all juices are thawed and blended.
Top with scoop of sherbet, if desired.
Makes 18 (4 ounce) servings.

title: tortoni squares
directions: Combine almonds, oleo, crumbs and extract; mix well.
Sprinkle 1/3 of crumbs over bottom of 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan that is lined with foil.
Spoon half of ice cream over crumbs.
Drizzle with preserves.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Repeat layers.
Store in freezer.
Cut in squares and garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until they begin to peak.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Continue to beat until mixture is stiff.
Fold in nuts and chips.
Turn oven off.
Spoon cookie mixture on cookie sheet (1 teaspoon).
Place in oven for 6 hours or overnight.
Store in airtight container.

title: zucchini-potato pancakes
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
In large bowl, combine zucchini, potatoes, eggs, cracker crumbs, salt, basil and pepper.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls into heated oil and cook until brown.
Add more oil, if needed.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes about 18 medium pancakes.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Boil chicken; cool and debone. Take bread and tear like you would for dressing. Mix seasoned salt, pepper, salt and onion with bread. Mix soups, broth and chicken. Add to bread crumbs and mix well. Put into two 9 x 13-inch pans. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Wash wild rice.
Boil rice for 15 minutes and drain; set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and discard all but 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in drippings, until onion is transparent.
Put in a large kettle and add rice, broth, mushrooms, soup and diced bacon.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour or more.
Do not add salt.

title: crepes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add flour and milk. Mix in slowly.
Put on a small frying pan with Crisco, 1/4 cup crepe batter.
Flip and fry both sides until golden brown.

title: italian cookie anise toast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat sugar and eggs for 5 minutes. Add anise and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix at low speed.
Make 3 separate long loaves on cookie sheet, 3-inches wide.
Bake 15 minutes, until lightly baked.
Remove from oven and cut into 1-inch cookies.
Put back on cookie sheet, cut side down, and bake 10 more minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lyn's dip
directions: Heat jello, cream cheese, tomato soup and water until melted and blended well.
Cool well.
Add Miracle Whip, pecans, bell pepper and onion; chill overnight.
Makes about 2-quarts of dip. Good for a large crowd and good with chips or vegetables.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Put rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Jell-O and sugar over rhubarb.
Sprinkle package of dry cake mix over mixture.
Mix butter and water together and drizzle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: best yet banana bread
directions: Mix in order given and pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apple, celery, nuts and mayonnaise.
Toss and serve on crisp greens.
Serves 4.

title: corn flake chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Dip each chicken breast in milk.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes or until done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream 1/3 of the sugar with butter and salt in a large bowl. Blend extract, 2 tablespoons milk and remaining sugar into mixture.
Gradually stir remaining milk into frosting until desired spreading consistency is reached.

title: punch bowl party dessert
directions: Bake cake in two round 8-inch cake pans according to package directions.
Cool.
Cut layers horizontally by pulling a string through.
You will have 4 layers.
Make pudding according to package directions.
Cool.
Mix 2 1/2 cups boiling water with 2 boxes of strawberry Jell-O, mixing until Jell-O dissolves.
Chill until slightly thickened (like egg white).
Assemble in a punch bowl as follows:
First, layer of cake, 1/4 of the Jell-O, layer of Cool Whip and layer of pudding.
Second layer of cake, Jell-O, Cool Whip and pudding.
Third layer of cake, Jell-O, Cool Whip and pudding.
Fourth layer of cake only, topped with thick layer of Cool Whip.
Garnish with fresh sliced berries.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 2 (5 x 9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rocky mt. apple pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Spread 1/2 mixture evenly in bottom of pie pan.
Line pan with quartered or halved apples, cut side up. Spread remaining sugar mixture on apples.
Drizzle cream over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy strawberry pie
directions: Crush crackers fine, then combine with sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Press firmly in unbuttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Mix milk and lemon juice by hand until thick.
Add strawberries and part of the juice for color.
Arrange in pie shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Beat into the wet mixture flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and vanilla.
Add nuts, dates and zucchini to mixture.

title: fruit tray and dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, jelly and coconut for dip mixture. Wash and cut fruit.
Arrange on tray.
Use decorative toothpicks to pick up fruit and dip in mixture.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix thoroughly. Store in refrigerator.
Serve with vegetables.

title: swedish coffee bread
directions: Beat together with enough cream to make it smooth.

title: cheese-stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small mixing bowl, combine green onions, parsley flakes, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Set aside.
Place 1 piece of cheese in center of each chicken breast. Top with 1/4 of onion mixture.
Starting at narrow edge, roll each breast tightly, tucking in sides to enclose cheese and onion mixture.
Dredge with flour.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip each rolled breast in beaten egg, then in crumb mixture to coat.

title: hot tuna melts
directions: Mix ingredients in order using 8 to 12 hamburger rolls.
Fill with mixture.
Cover with tops.
Seal each sandwich inside of foil and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and rinse in cold water.
Gradually blend milk and mayonnaise into cream cheese.
Add seasonings and shrimp.

title: the cake that won't last
directions: Mash
bananas
in
mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir until blended by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sprinkle cinnamon on and beat.
Set mixture aside. Break bread into bite size pieces in a bowl.
Pour water over bread; make soggy.
Squeeze water out of bread by handfuls.
Put all bread in baking dish.
Pour egg and milk mixture over it. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion for 10 minutes until soft and drain. Melt butter and place croutons in skillet.
Place them on bottom of cake pan and save the other half for the top.
Grate carrots, and mix with mushroom soup, chicken soup and King sour; mix them with squash.
Grate cheese on top.
Place Italian bread crumbs on top sparingly and bake 30 minutes at 350° or longer.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meats; drain.
Saute garlic in oil.
Add mushrooms, basil, oregano, tomatoes, paste, salt, pepper, sugar, 1 cup water and meat.
Simmer about 45 minutes.

title: broccoli pasta
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets.
Peel and slice stems.
Cook pasta.
When pasta has about 13 minutes left to cook, heat olive oil and add garlic and red pepper.
Stir one minute.
Add broccoli.
Mix well.
Add salt and 1/2 cup water or defatted broth.
Use less salt if using canned all chicken broth.
Cover with a tight lid.
Cook 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain pasta and mix with broccoli and its liquid.
Serve at once.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a casserole dish and top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garden pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and press together. Bake as directed on can until brown.
Mix remaining ingredients except vegetables and spread over crust. Top with vegetables.

title: country pork ribs
directions: Rub ribs with crushed garlic and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place in roasting pan, rib side down,in 350° oven.
While ribs are roasting, put dried fruit in saucepan, barely cover with water and simmer covered for 35 minutes.
After ribs have cooked for 1 hour, add the fruit and its cooking liquid and continue roasting for an additional 30 minutes.
Make glaze by combining unsweetened orange juice concentrate, onion flakes and mustard.
Spread over ribs and roast another 15 minutes, basting frequently.
If ribs don't appear nicely browned, bake a little longer until they have a pleasing color.
Cut the ribs into serving size pieces and arrange along with the fruit on a platter.
A green vegetable and salad will finish meal.

title: pineapple date bread
directions: Combine egg, milk, shortening, pineapple, nuts and dates. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to first mixture and stir just to moisten. Grease baking pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
A nice holiday bread.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Chill before serving.

title: lazy macaroons
directions: Beat the egg whites with a dash of vanilla until stiff. Slowly add sugar and fold in the coconut. Drop by a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet and bake about 20 minutes at 325°.
Makes about 20.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine eggs, breadcrumbs, tomato juice, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir in ground beef, mixing well with hands.
On waxed paper, pat meat to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle. Arrange ham slices on top of meat, leaving a small margin around edge.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat, using paper to lift; seal edges and ends.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Place cheese wedges over top of roll.
Return to oven for 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Serve with watermelon pickle or sweet relish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease baking dish and sprinkle bottom evenly with onion gravy mix.
Spread rice evenly over the mix.
Cut up chickens; salt and pepper.
Place pieces on rice.
Mix soup with 1 1/2 cans of water and pour over the chicken.
Cover with heavy foil and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt, stirring constantly over low heat, the first three ingredients.
Add Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Drop by the teaspoon on waxed paper and enjoy.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix with sugar; stir in milk.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Sweeten fruit to taste and pour over batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Enjoy.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowers in small pieces.
Cook bacon and crumble. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over all other ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice (unsalted).
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together. Cook at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
May also be put in microwave for approximately 20 minutes.

title: granny's chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add shortening. Mix until it's a cornmeal type texture.
Add egg and enough water to make it "a little wetter than pie crust dough." Roll out onto floured board and cut into squares.
Drop into boiling chicken and broth. Add salt and black pepper to taste and thicken broth with more flour.
Dumplings should be ready in 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Prepare brownie mix according to pkg. directions. Cut a circle of parchment paper (not wax paper) to fit the 15 inch large round stone. Pour brownie mix onto parchment paper. Spread into 14 inch circle. Bake 15-18 minutes or until brownie is set. Do no overbake. Cool completely. Mix cream cheese, drained pineapple and sugar, spread on brownie. Slice bananas and strawberries and arrange over the mixture. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and drizzle chocolate topping over. Refrigerate. Cut into 16 wedges.

title: pinylata or sausage rolls
directions: Mix flour with hot roll mix flour.
Use yeast from mix plus extra yeast, dissolved in the warm water.
Mix yeast water into flour and mix until dough comes away from side of bowl.
Add maybe 1/2 cup flour more and knead 1 minute.
Cover and let rise 1/2 hour.
Roll 1/3 of dough to size of 10-inch pie shell.
Spread 1/3 of cooked and drained sausage on top with some Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and bread crumbs sprinkled on.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Cut into 3-inch pieces or smaller.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Do 3 times.

title: cathy's crab brunch casserole
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Spread layer of croutons in buttered 9-inch square casserole.
Sprinkle with crabmeat, then cheese.
Layer 2 times, ending with cheese layer.
Beat eggs; add milk and seasonings.
Pour over casserole.
Bake in oven preheated to 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Check for doneness by inserting knife in center.
Will come out clean when finished.
Sprinkle bacon on top about 10 minutes before finished baking.

title: cheesy baked mostaccioli
directions: Brown meat good; cut up vegetables.
Add mushrooms, soup, onion, pepper and celery.
Cook 45 minutes, then add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add cooked noodles to the mixture.
Put mixture in a large casserole dish and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Mix strawberries with glaze; set aside.
Break cake into bite size pieces.
Fold together pudding, Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Layer cake, pudding mixture and strawberries in a punch bowl until reaches top.
You may garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix salt, sugar and mayonnaise and pour over the vegetables. Sprinkle with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream
sugars
and margarine;
add eggs, one at a time, beating
well
after each.
Measure cocoa in measuring cup and fill
to
the
3/4 mark with boiling water.
Stir to dissolve. Stir
into
creamed mixture.
Mix soda with buttermilk and add to the
creamed
mixture alternately with flour, mixing well. Pour into
two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamed chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place cheese slices over chicken.
Combine soup and wine.
Stir.
Spoon sauce evenly over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle with stuffing. Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
