Spread graham crackers. Add butterscotch morsels, then chocolate morsels, then nuts and coconut.
Then pour Eagle Brand milk over layers.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all but the last four ingredients in a large bowl and set aside.
Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Grease an iron skillet. Heat and sprinkle with a thin layer of raw corn meal, brown slightly.
Pour 1/2 of the corn meal batter into the skillet; sprinkle with the meat, cheese, onion and chiles.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake in 9-inch skillet at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: italian rolls
directions: Bring 2 cups water to a boil.
Pour over oil, sugar and salt. Cook
until
only
lukewarm.
Dissolve
yeast in 1/3 c. warm water.
Add
to
cooled mixture along with the eggs and 3 cups flour.
Stir
until
smooth.
Add
remaining 3 cups flour and blend in.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead lightly.
Shape
into rolls and place on greased pans (I use 9 x 13-inch pans).
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sugared popcorn
directions: Combine sugar, butter and water in large, heavy pot. Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Continue to cook until the sugar is dissolved and the mixture becomes syrupy, 4 to 5 minutes. Remove pot from heat. Add the popcorn to the pot. Stir to coat popcorn evenly with sugar mixture. Turn coated popcorn out in thin layer onto sheet of wax paper or parchment paper. Let popcorn cool for about 10 minutes. Serve in a basket or for a festive touch, in individual paper cones.

title: mock black forest cake for microwave oven
directions: Grease or spray with Pam, a microwave Bundt cake pan. Sprinkle nuts and put cherries in bottom of pan.
Put mixture in pan, only 1/2 full.
Bake on High for 13 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Dump
pie
filling
and pineapple with juice into it.
Dump yellow cake mix on top and spread
it
around.
Drizzle with butter
or
margarine.
Dump nuts and some coconut on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry onion and bell peppers in oil until tender.
Cook over low to medium heat.
Add tomatoes, water, onions, peppers, rice, salt and black pepper.
Stir constantly until done.
Serve with crumbled cornbread or cooked cabbage, if desired.

title: healthy supper
directions: Cook meat in large pot.
Add rice, bouillon (dissolved in hot water) and seasoned salt and stir.
Add cabbage, onions and carrots.
Cover and cook slowly until cabbage cooks down and carrots are tender.
Can be simmered for an hour and left unattended.
Serve with soy sauce, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown hamburger. Cook noodles according to box directions. In large container, combine ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Top with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and salt in 2 cups water, about 20 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Lightly mash with potato masher and cook, stirring constantly, until soup is hot and thickened.

title: corn and english pea salad
directions: Drain corn and peas.
Stir in other ingredients until mixed well.
Chill at least 12 hours.

title: chilled summer soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add the lettuce, watercress and spring onions and fry for 8 minutes.
Stir in all but 3 tablespoons of the chicken stock and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Blend the flour to a paste with the remaining stock and stir into the soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste and continue cooking until soup has thickened.
Puree in an electric blender. Cool, then stir in cream.
Sprinkle top with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tempting drop sugar cookies
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature; sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together margarine, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add the egg; cream until mixture is fluffy. Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth; blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet; flatten the dough with the bottom of a glass which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: shredded sweet potatoes
directions: *May vary amounts as desired.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix together chicken, broth, soup and vegetables.
Spread into oblong baking dish.
Mix flour, margarine and milk; spread over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients, then add next 5 ingredients.
Combine water, oil and eggs.
Mix together dry and wet mixtures well.
Add raisins and/or pecans to taste.
Bake at 350° for one hour in loaf pans.

title: layered salad
directions: Put sliced lettuce in bottom of bowl or container you are using (glass allows you to see the layers).
Put the other layers of vegetables you are using; try to vary colors for a nice look. The choice is yours, except that you need to finish with the peas on top.
Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar in small bowl; spread over entire top of salad, on top of peas.
Cover; refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
To serve, go down to bottom of bowl with salad fork and spoon to get all the layers and dressing.

title: nutty o's
directions: A blessing be upon the COOK

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk, until well blended. Pour into large greased tube pan or two loaf pans.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until smooth. Drain chilies. Gently stir in chilies, tomatoes and onion.
Put in serving bowl and chill. Serve with taco chips or Triscuits.
Makes 2 cups.

title: ginger bread
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, molasses and water.
Sift dry ingredients into mixture and blend well.
Stir in eggs.
Pour in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and some of the chopped fresh fruit.
Spoon into crust. Chill.
Arrange fresh fruit on top.

title: banana fudge brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of an 8-inch square pan. Melt in a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, the butter and chocolate chips.
Beat in the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake for about 30 minutes. Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 14 or 16.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Arrange
cubes
on
bottom
of
dish.	Fold
crabmeat, mayonnaise,
onion, celery and green pepper together and spoon over cubed	bread.	Trim
4 to 6 slices bread and arrange over crabmeat mixture.
Beat
eggs
and milk together and pour over mixture.
Chill
8	hours or longer.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake uncovered
for 15 minutes.
Take out and spread soup over bread and
top
with cheese and paprika and cook for one hour, covered.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; pour off grease.
Bring water to boil.
Add soup; boil for 7 minutes.
Add to sausage and vegetables.
Pour into greased casserole pan; sprinkle sliced almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pancake mix
directions: Sift flour and baking powder into bowl.
Add milk, melted shortening and egg.
Beat well. Pour onto sprayed pan.
(For thinner pancakes, add more milk.)
Makes 12 to 15 (5-inch) pancakes.

title: bean soup
directions: Saute together garlic, pepper, and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add 1 or 2 cans water.
Simmer until peppers are done.

title: baked beans with ground beef
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery.
Brown ground beef.
Mix beans, barbecue sauce, catsup and brown sugar.
Add beef and sauteed vegetables.
Mix everything together.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sweet and sour cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, eggs, soup mix and Accent.
Roll into bite size pieces.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Arrange rolls in well-greased, fluted tube pan.
Sprinkle pudding (dry) over rolls.
Cook butter and remaining ingredients over low heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture bubbles.
Pour over rolls.
Cover tightly with foil.
Let stand overnight on counter.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then invert carefully onto serving dish.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite-size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 462°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, the 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary as most people do not like to find hare in their stew. Yield:
3,800 servings.

title: fresh mint jelly
directions: Wash mint, leaving stems intact.
Crush or coarsely chop. Place in a large saucepan.
Add sugar, water and vinegar.
Over high heat, bring to a full rolling boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs (save some for the top), sugar and melted margarine and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add eggs, remaining 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla and cream well.
Pour cream cheese mixture over crust and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Spread pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Top with whipped cream and the rest of graham cracker crumbs.
Chill overnight.

title: lolita's deep dish apple pie
directions: Mix sugar and apples.
Arrange sliced apples into chilled shell 1/2-inch from edge; work toward center until shell is covered.
Add salt, cinnamon, grated rind of lemon and lemon juice to apple mixture in pie shell.
Pile remaining apples on top.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and seal edges.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious frozen strawberry salad(salad or dessert)
directions: Cream together Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese.
Fold remaining ingredients into mixture.
Place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and freeze or you may put in individual foil muffin cups and freeze. Enjoy.
Serves 10.

title: fresh blueberry cake
directions: Cream the butter and then add sugar a little at a time, creaming again.
Add eggs and some flour, sifted with the salt and baking powder.
Blend slowly, adding milk and the rest of the flour. Wash blueberries; dry with paper towel and dust with flour. Add to batter just before baking.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar, nutmeg, cloves or whatever appeals to you.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: popovers
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add salt and sift again.
Beat eggs with rotary or electric beater until light and thick.
Add flour and 1/3 cup of the milk; continue to beat slowly until all the flour is moistened, about 30 seconds.
Gradually add remaining milk and melted shortening.
Beat until free from lumps, 1 to 2 minutes. Fill greased muffin pan.
Divide in 6 to 8 large popovers.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients
well
except
for 1 cup of pecans. Shape into ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Best if chilled a day or two ahead of serving time.

title: pintos and sausage
directions: Cook beans as directed on bag (I use more water, to give some juice), around 2 1/2 hours.
Cut up sausage.
Add to beans.
Cook about 15 minutes more.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Great with cornbread and onions.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan put nuts and coconut on bottom of pan and spread evenly.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt oleo and cream cheese in microwave or low heat in pan.
When melted, mix in powdered sugar; should be pretty thick.
Spoon all over cake mix; do not spread out.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You don't have to ice cake unless you want to.

title: low-fat carrot cake
directions: Mix the first eight ingredients.
Heat to boil and then simmer 5 minutes.
Cool to warm and add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan 45 to 60 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: holiday salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as directed.
When partly congealed, add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into mold and chill to firm.

title: colorful vegetable salad
directions: Layer half of vegetables in a salad bowl.
Repeat layers.
Add salad dressing.
Cover tightly and chill until ready to serve.

title: oriental brussels sprouts
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towel.
Stir soy sauce into the bacon drippings.
Add chestnuts, garlic and broth.
Bring to a boil and add Brussels sprouts. Return to a boil; cover and reduce heat, cooking about 8 minutes or until sprouts are just tender.
Combine cornstarch and water and add to the pan liquid.
Cook, stirring, until thickened. Sprinkle reserved bacon over the top to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal crunchies cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add brown sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Form dough into small balls.
Dip tops in a little additional granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Boil maybe 1 or 2 minutes, no longer or they will get too hard.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir together.
Add Rice Krispies.
Put in bar pan, greased with butter or margarine.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix everything together and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 35 minutes or until browned slightly.
Let stand 2 or 3 minutes and cut into 1-inch squares. Serve warm as hors d'oeuvres.

title: easy casserole
directions: Fry meat until no longer pink.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook until tender.
Drain off excess fat.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In a large pot, cook chicken and spices in water for several hours, until done.
The meat will start falling off the bone. Take chicken out, remove meat from bone and set aside.

title: hinder wings
directions: Mix together.
Use only 2 larger sections of wings.
Put wings in a shallow pan; pour sauce over.
Baste and turn every 15 minutes so they get covered with sauce.
Last 10 minutes, sprinkle with sesame seed.
Drain on cake racks (spread newspaper underneath to catch drippings).
Can be eaten cold.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Tear up bread in dish, brown and drain sausage, spoon over bread and sprinkle on grated cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper; pour mixture over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can prepare the night before. Serves 6.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream
the shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately
with
milk.
Stir thoroughly after each addition. Pour batter in two 9-inch greased and floured pans and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: wanda's lasagna
directions: Boil noodles until done.
Brown hamburger meat.
In a large bowl, combine hamburger meat, Ragu sauce, sour cream, cottage cheese, salt and garlic powder.

title: lemon-lime jello salad
directions: Mix both packages of Jell-O in the hot water.
Let cool.
Add pineapple, milk, salad dressing, cheese and pecans.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Cut in squares.
If desired, top with fresh mint leaf and red and green cherries.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots just until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients in a pan.
Bring to a boil and pour over cooked carrots. Refrigerate.
Will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Sauce left after other ingredients have been eaten can be used over salads.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot baked potatoes in half.
Scoop out insides; reserve shells.
In large bowl, with electric mixer, beat potatoes and spread until creamy.
Gradually beat in milk; stir in onion, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into reserved shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Arrange in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion; drain. Mash.
Add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain. Cook and stir onion in bacon drippings until tender and gold. Stir in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat.
Stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boil; stir constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Crumble bacon.
Dice potatoes.
Carefully stir bacon and potatoes in hot mixture.
Heat through.
Stir to coat potatoes.

title: coleslaw superb
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, green pepper and sugar.
In saucepan, combine 1 tablespoon sugar, salt, celery seed, dry mustard, water, vinegar and oil.
Bring to a boil; pour over vegetables.
Cool in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Keeps for 3 weeks.

title: delicious meatballs and gravy
directions: Chop onion; add garlic to oil in a large pot.
Saute until soft (do not burn).
Strain tomatoes.
Add this to the onions and garlic, plus puree, salt, black pepper, water and sugar.
Cook this for 1 hour, low to medium heat.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.

title: pasta
directions: For pasta, drop penne into kettle of boiling water; return to boil and boil gently for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain; toss with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Return to pan and keep warm. For sauce, saute garlic slowly in 3 tablespoons olive oil in skillet until softened, but not browned.
Add olives, basil, red pepper and tomato sauce.
Heat.
Stir in cheeses and heat, stirring until chunks begin to melt.
Pour over pasta.
Pass additional grated Parmesan cheese to sprinkle over if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: cold avocado and tomato soup(gazpacho)
directions: Put all ingredients into a serving tureen, stir and chill well. To serve, spoon into individual soup bowls and top each with a slice of avocado and put an ice cube in each bowl.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Make meat balls.
Cook meat balls in the tomato soup, 1 can water and 1/3 to 1/2 can Healthy Choice spaghetti sauce.
Let simmer for a while, then add spaghetti that has already been cooked.

title: strawberry frozen yogurt(diabetic)
directions: In a large saucepan, soften gelatin in water for 2 minutes. Place over medium heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Add evaporated milk, 1/2 cup of the fructose and salt to gelatin.
Stir over medium heat until well blended, approximately 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in yogurt and vanilla.
Set aside.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix together and slice apples to dip.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half.
Cook in boiling salted water until done; drain.
While still warm, combine spaghetti with eggs and Parmesan.
Pour into a well greased 10-inch pie plate and pat mixture up and around sides with a spoon.

title: baked eggs
directions: Layer in order in a small baking dish.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Serves one.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Use the pineapple juice and enough cold water to make the 2 cups cold liquid.
Add to Jell-O and let set until it starts to congeal.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: teriyaki steak strips
directions: Combine all ingredients
(except flank steak).	Marinate flank steak overnight.
Grill.

title: orange-kissed pancakes
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl.

title: fix ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water.
Drain and mash with the rest of the ingredients except for the melted butter.
Spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well. Add 3/4 cup pecans and mix. Shape into a ring and pat remaining pecans on top. Chill. (Put on platter or on sheet of wax paper.)

title: collards and cornbread
directions: Wash greens thoroughly (2 to 3 times) to remove sand.
Take out and discard tough stems.
Put ham hocks or ham chunks in pot.
Add greens and fill half full with water.
Let greens come to a boil, then turn fire down and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until seasoned and tender.
Add salt according to taste when serving.
Lift greens out of water into a flat bowl and cut into bite size pieces with a sharp knife.
We like to sprinkle pepper sauce or vinegar on our plates.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Mix together the milk, crackers, coconut, salt and sugar; scald.
Pour about a cup of this hot mixture over the egg yolks. Blend egg and hot milk together before returning to hot mixture. Cook until thick; add vanilla.
Pour into baking dish and cover with meringue.

title: fruit cocktail
directions: Blend with ice and strain champagne flute. Garnish with strawberry.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and cook beef and onion until meat is browned.
Drain fat off, then add bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add mushrooms with liquid.
Combine sour cream and flour; blend into meat mixture.
Continue cooking about 5 minutes or until thickened.
Cook noodles to package directions.
Drain; serve stroganoff over hot cooked noodles.

title: *sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots in slightly salted water for 15 minutes.
Add pepper and cook for 3 minutes more; drain.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add water to juice to make 1/3 cup.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, liquid, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add vegetables and pineapple.
Heat through. Serves 6.

title: chinese chicken and broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Toss chicken, cornstarch, salt and white pepper in glass or plastic bowl. Cover.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine ingredients in large skillet.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Stir and cook 3 more minutes.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: ole settlers baked beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion, then add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour all ingredients into a large baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: paper cup salad
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, sugar, salt, pineapple, bananas and coloring.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon into paper muffin cup liners in muffin tins and freeze.
When frozen remove from tins. Put in plastic bags or airtight container and return to freezer. Will keep for several months.
Take out of freezer for 15 minutes before serving.
Peel off liners and serve on lettuce.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: no bake orange coconut balls
directions: Melt butter and pour over vanilla wafer crumbs and add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls and then roll in the coconut.
Place on cookie sheet to let harden.

title: pork chop cheese pillows
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, melt butter. Saute onion and garlic clove until soft; set aside.
Stab small holes in pork chops and sprinkle lightly with garlic powder and seasoned salt.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Boil ham bone, water, bay leaf, peppercorns and cloves.
Add beans; boil 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Last half hour, add the rest of ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 6 cups.

title: italian squash pie(low-fat)
directions: Cook vegetables in microwave or skillet sprayed with vegetable spray until tender.
Add cheese to egg substitute.
Add seasonings; mix well.
Place pie crust in glass pie plate; spread mustard on bottom of crust.
Add vegetables.
Pour cheese and egg mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy combination in a pastry shell
directions: Make the white sauce by melting butter in a large skillet. Take off the heat and add flour to make a paste.
Add milk, return to heat and stir constantly until thick and smooth.

title: amish raisin cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add milk and 2 slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Add salt, vanilla, oleo and cooled raisins.
Pour into baked crust.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix egg and Parmesan cheese together.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix in 1 tablespoon butter, then mix into spaghetti with the egg and Parmesan cheese.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with a little oil.

title: hawaiian delight pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, put in pie shell and chill.

title: meat loaf with sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a saucepan, mix tomato sauce with brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Combine egg, onion, crackers, meat, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce mixture.
Mix lightly but thoroughly and shape into loaf.
Put into baking dish and pour remainder of tomato sauce over mixture over it.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, basting occasionally. Note:
This recipe may be cut in half and it works fine.

title: no-bake peanut nuggets
directions: Heat sugar and milk in saucepan to boiling.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add saltine crumbs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well so that peanut butter is melted.
Add coconut and peanuts and stir until mixture is stiff.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper to form mounds.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine vegetables and chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour liquids over chicken and cover with crust.

title: crisp candy bars
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In saucepan, mix syrup and sugar, stirring
frequently
to boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat. Stir
in peanut butter, then cereal and press into pan.
Melt your chips and spread while hot.

title: plains, georgia cheese ring
directions: Mix cheese, onion, pecans and mayonnaise together.
Mold mixture with a spoon or hands into a ring.
Fill the center with strawberry preserves. Serve with Ritz crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach stuffed eggs
directions: Remove shells.
Cut eggs in half; remove yolks.
Mix yolks with ingredients; beat until smooth, adding a little cream if necessary.
Sprinkle red pepper for garnish.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mix well.
May be kept a week or more in refrigerator.

title: bread stuffing for turkey
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of butter until soft but not brown.
Combine with the bread, seasonings and stock.

title: lemony torte squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour.
Batter will be stiff. Pack in 9 x9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add zucchini, garlic, salt and pepper. Cook 5 minutes until zucchini is bright green.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add cheese, parsley, rice and thyme.
Add to zucchini mixture and place in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup bread crumbs and drizzle with olive oil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients and stir constantly over medium heat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring to boil and cook for 5 minutes while stirring.
Then add remaining ingredients.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Prepare stuffing mix according to box directions.
In a 11 x 13-inch baking dish, layer all ingredients in order listed.
Top with a little Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mash bananas and add last so that they will not turn dark.
Bake at 300 degrees in a muffin tin or loaf pan.

title: rice casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Mix uncooked rice, mushroom soup and dry onion soup together.
Add water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
May need to add water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender according to package directions. Combine eggs, soup, cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold in broccoli. Pour into casserole dish, cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: monterey beans and cheese
directions: Fry the first 3 ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients. Cook, slowly, stirring until blended, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle 1/4 to 1/2 pound Cheddar cheese on top.
Put lid on for 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve on top of rice or mix with rice. Serve with carrots.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole dish.
Stir in rice, water and soup.
Add green pepper, onion and pimentos, all chopped. Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Drain cottage cheese in sieve.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients well and let rise in same bowl until doubled. Work down with spoon and transfer to 2 oiled loaf pans.
Let rise again.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: benedict spread
directions: Mash cream cheese with grated cucumber pulp.
Add onion, salt and enough mayonnaise to make a smooth spread.
Add small amount of green food coloring to make filling a very pale green.
This is one of my favorites.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift flour and sugar together. Mix margarine, cocoa and water in a saucepan. Bring to a rapid boil. Pour over flour and sugar mixture and stir until well mixed. Add eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix well and pour into well-greased 11 x 16-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: berries 'n bits trifle
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 2 cups pudding into 3-quart glass bowl.
Top with 1/2 of each of the vanilla wafers, berries, little chocolate bits and remaining pudding.
Repeat layers.
Garnish with additional little bits, wafers and berries.
Chill thoroughly.
Refrigerate any leftovers. Serves 8 to 10.
An elegant, delicious treat.

title: sweet relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add salt.
Let drain on a towel 2 hours.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cook until done.
Boil. Cook about 15 minutes.
Put in jars and cool.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until cheese melts, approximately 20 minutes.
Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: plan ahead pinto beans
directions: Note:
Sprouting the beans helps to remove some of the gas and also brings in extra nutrients.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt half of shortening and add cocoa.
Set aside.
Cream the rest of the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then cocoa mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Chill 30 minutes.
Drop by spoonful into powdered sugar and roll.
Place on greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form dough. Roll into bite-size balls. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes about 30 balls. Serve hot. Freezes well also.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix water and salad dressing.
Mix the two together gradually and beat.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. May make 1 layer or a 2-layer cake.

title: 3 layer pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly; put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix all these together and cool slightly. Pour in casserole dish with a small bag of miniature marshmallows. Let gel.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Stir in chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition at high speed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a cooled 9-inch pie shell.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: cranberry cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries. Reserve juice. Set cherries aside. Add water to juice to measure 1 cup. Transfer to saucepan. Bring to a boil. Add cherry gelatin; stir until dissolved. Whisk in cranberry sauce until smooth. Add cherries; pour into an 11 x 7 pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: hamburger with baked beans
directions: Cut bacon strips in small pieces.
Add onion and saute.
Brown ground beef with the onion and bacon.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into casserole or baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Place one pie shell in bottom of casserole dish. Layer soups, vegetables and chicken. Place second pie shell on top and slit with knife several times. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden and bubbly.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with cherries and crushed nuts. Chill.

title: millionaire pie - no bake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and beat for 5 min.
Pour into shell, mix next three ingredients and spread over first layer. Chill and serve.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Saute meat and drain on paper towel.
Combine all ingredients in large stewpot.
Cook until okra turns color.

title: southern sweet tea
directions: Bring the 2 cups of water to a rolling boil. Drop the tea bags in the water and then the soda. Cook about 1 minute. Cover with lid and remove from heat or just turn the burner off. Let steep (sit) for about 15 minutes. Put sugar in a 2-quart pitcher and pour hot tea in and stir to dissolve. Add enough cold water to fill the pitcher. Add the lemon juice and serve over ice.

title: shrimp-corn chowder soup
directions: Cook onions with butter until tender.
Add rest of the ingredients and heat to boiling.
Put pat of butter or oleo in each bowl and fill with chowder.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Mix rice, soup mix, soup, water and wine in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Put chicken parts on top. Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour until chicken is done.

title: sprite sherbet punch
directions: In a punch bowl add 2 1/2 qts. of softened sherbet. Add Sprite gently, DO NOT STIR. Add remaining 1/2 qt. sherbet by scoopfulls and float on punch. Serves approx. 30 people.

title: apricot almond brie
directions: Remove top rind from cheese; place cheese on serving plate. In a small saucepan, combine preserves and liqueur.
Heat until mixture is hot, but not boiling.
Pour some of the sauce over cheese (save remainder for adding later, if desired).
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and tomato
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake, covered, 15 minutes in oven preheated to 425°; drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Pour heated sauce over chicken; top with cheese. Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: briar patch bake
directions: Brown meat; stir in barbecue sauce and onion.
Heat.
Prepare macaroni dinner as directed on the package except use 1/2 cup milk. Layer half the dinner in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining dinner.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onions until done in skillet.
Cook macaroni and mix with hamburger.
Put in a large casserole dish. Add diced up cheese (about 4 slices).
Add pimientos and tomato soup.
Cover with more cheese slices and crumbled up bread on top of casserole.
Bake until cheese melts and bread is brown.

title: homemade muenster cheese
directions: Don't let new small potatoes go to waste.
Scrape them or if you want to do a basketful or more, fill your washing machine with cold water and let it run to clean them.
Pack them in jars; add water and 1 teaspoon salt to each quart.
Cold pack 3 hours.

title: rigatoni and cheese sauce
directions: Prepare rigatoni according to package directions. Melt margarine.
Add flour and cook, stirring constantly for 2 minutes. Do not brown.
Stir in milk, salt, pepper and cheese.
Cook until smooth and thickened.
Pour sauce over hot rigatoni and mix gently.
Sprinkle peas on top and place in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: green chili fritters
directions: Mix salt, masa and flour into bowl. Add beaten egg, milk and shortening. Drop chili into batter, then drop chili in hot oil.

title: best-ever corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir together.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch dish in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato deluxe
directions: After
topping	has been added, bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Potatoes	may be prepared several days ahead and refrigerated.
Topping should not be added until you are ready to bake them.

title: pistachio jello salad
directions: Mix all together and chill thoroughly before serving.

title: egg pudding
directions: Put cubed bread on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and cheese in double boiler.
Pour over bread.
Beat eggs with fork and add milk and mix.
Pour over mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake one hour at 300°.

title: quick cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage in bowl.
Add pinch of celery seed or more, if desired.
Add cole slaw dressing and stir.
Chill and serve or serve immediately.

title: sour cream yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water; let stand while combining sour cream, sugar and baking soda in large bowl.
Add 2 cups biscuit mix, then yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 3 more cups biscuit mix.
Turn dough onto board dusted with 1/2 cup biscuit mix; knead to form smooth ball.
Shape dough into small rounds the size of a walnut. Place close together in buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake rolls 15 minutes, or until done.
Makes 72 bite size rolls.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Cut cabbage, onions and green pepper very thin and sprinkle with salt.
Bring to boil oil, vinegar and sugar.
Let cool.
Pour over vegetables.
(Better if made one day in advance.)

title: coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven at 200°.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Mix ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cocoa oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk to a boil for about 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Then drop on waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: green beans
directions: Wash and break beans into bite size pieces.
Wash new potatoes.
Cook in a large pot on top of stove until tender. Season to taste.

title: zucchini-carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pans (three 5 1/2 x 9 1/2 x 3-inch if double).
In large bowl, beat eggs with oil.
Stir in sugar, zucchini, carrots and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Blend into egg and oil, etc. and add raisins.
Bake 1 hour or until tested with toothpick. Remove from pan and cool.

title: butterscotch balls
directions: Soften butter (don't melt).
Mix powdered sugar, peanut butter, graham crackers, vanilla, coconut and butter in large bowl.
Roll into 1-inch balls.

title: english trifle
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan according to directions on box.
This only uses half the cake (you can find someone baking on the same day and share).
Break 1/4 of the cake into large pieces and place in a 2-quart serving bowl.
Pour half the thawed strawberries over the cake.
Spread with half of prepared pudding.
Repeat layers. Chill at least 8 hours.
Right before serving, spread whipped topping on top and sprinkle with almonds.
Spoon into dessert dishes to serve.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a graham cracker pie crust and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: shrimp and green noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Line a casserole with noodles and make into a nest.
In a large frying pan, saute the shrimp in 1/2 cup clarified butter until pink and tender, about 5 minutes.
Cover noodles with shrimp.
Combine soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and chives; add mustard and sherry.
Pour sauce over shrimp and sprinkle Cheddar cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until
cheese has melted and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells.
Freeze until firm.
Serve immediately.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry onions and garlic in oil until soft, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add hamburger and cook until brown.
Mix in salt, pepper, rosemary and tomato paste.
Gradually add hot water and simmer 30 minutes uncovered.
In bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a thin layer of sauce, then a layer of cooked noodles, layer of cottage cheese, layer of Mozzarella cheese, then repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Blend Crisco with salt and sugars.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Add flour, baking soda and nuts to mixture. Shape into roll about 2 1/2 inches in diameter or 2 smaller rolls. Roll in wax paper and chill in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, slice thinly and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or when delicately brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients into carrots. Place in refrigerator and let set 12 hours or more. Yields 1/2 gallon or enough for 25 people.

title: quaker choc oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: orange salad
directions: Cook Jell-O, pudding and water until thick and clear.
Chill. Add whipped Dream Whip and oranges.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Stir in Baby Ruth pieces and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and blend well. Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Remove from baking sheet onto wire racks to cool.
To enhance flavoring, add caramel flavoring.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all together and shape into loaf pan.
Decorate top with pecans and cherries, if wanted.
Can use marshmallows.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast mixture.
Add to dry ingredients.
Dough should be soft and pliable; work 5 minutes.
Roll out; cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
May refrigerate dough overnight.

title: land and sea linguini
directions: Place water on stove for linguini; follow directions on package to cook the pasta.
Place all ingredients, except mussels, into large pot and simmer for 1/2 hour.
While the sausage and sauce are cooking, clean mussels according to package directions.
Add to sauce and cook for another 15 to 20 minutes until mussel shells open.
Serve over linguini.
Serves about 8.

title: erin's orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with cottage cheese until well blended.
Add fruit; be sure oranges and pineapple are drained well.
Mix well and fold in Cool Whip.
Makes a great low-cal, cool salad.

title: louisiana pie
directions: Pour pie filling in buttered deep-dish pie pan. Pour dry cake mix over pie filling. Slice butter evenly over cake mix. Bake at 350° until crust is brown (approximately 30 minutes). Stir mixture 1 time while baking. Good served with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: glazed onion rings
directions: Peel onions and cut into even thin slices. Heat margarine in large skillet. Add onions; toss until coated with margarine. Do not brown. Add vinegar, brown sugar and curry powder. Blend well. Add parsley. Cook 2 to 3 minutes until glazed. Season with salt, pepper and curry powder. Serve hot as a side dish or cook as an appetizer. Can be used in greens or potato salad.

title: chocolate peanut butter bonbons
directions: In large bowl, combine vanilla frosting, peanut butter and margarine until well blended.
Stir in crumbs; mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Chill 1 hour.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together using only 1 package of pudding for 4 minutes at high speed.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Beat together 1 package of pudding and 1 cup milk.
Beat heavy cream until peaks form. Mix with pudding mixture.
Use this to ice cake when cake is cool. Store cake in refrigerator.

title: day-ahead salad
directions: Tear lettuce in pieces.
Cook and drain peas.
Layer vegetables in a large salad bowl.
Spread a layer of mayonnaise, sealing the lettuce.
Make a second layer of vegetables.
Seal with mayonnaise.
Top with Parmesan cheese and then black olives. Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine whole wheat flour and yeast.
Heat buttermilk, molasses, honey, salt and butter until warm.
Add oats, whole wheat flour, yeast mixture and eggs.
Bake at low speed for 3 minutes at medium.

title: dried beef snax
directions: Spread
cream cheese on slice of dried beef.
Put slice of pickle
on
top
and roll up.
Chill, then slice into bite size pieces.

title: cheese log
directions: Note:
About 1 cup to 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans for outside coating.

title: ada's carrot-pineapple jello salad
directions: Dilute lemon jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and pineapple juice.
Let cool.
Add the crushed pineapple and 1 cup shredded carrots.
Chill until set.

title: stew
directions: Fry bacon in a large stew pot.
Remove bacon.
Add stew meat and sear.
Lower heat and add tomatoes, beef broth, water, celery, onion, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Remove 1/4 cup broth from stew.
Cool and mix with flour.
Add flour mixture to stew.
Season.
Add carrots and potatoes and cook 30 minutes.
Add corn and bacon.
Cook another 5 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Put beans in a baking dish and add onions, mustard, brown sugar and bacon.
Stir to mix. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 1 hour until bubbly and set.

title: electric 4-alarm chili
directions: In large, heavy pot, brown beef with onions, green pepper and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except kidney beans.
Simmer, uncovered, at least 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When thickened, stir in drained beans.
Heat through and serve.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into large pieces.
Combine all ingredients, except butter; shake in a large bag.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put potatoes in one layer.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Turn once during baking.

title: tammy's chicken fingers
directions: Beat the eggs in a large bowl and add enough buttermilk to cover the chicken strips. Stir. Coat chicken strips and refrigerate overnight.
Remove chicken strips from mixture and shake off excess.
Dip in a mixture of flour, salt, pepper and the seasoned salt. Deep fry until chicken strips are golden brown and drain on a paper towel.

title: scrambled tots
directions: In a large frypan, put layer of Tater Tots to cover skillet. Cook Tater Tots until just about done.
Mash Tater Tots flat with a spatula.
Break open about 4 or 5 eggs over the top of Tater Tots.
Mix eggs in with Tater Tots. Season to taste.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured tube pan or make three 9-inch layers. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and light corn syrup until thickened.
After cooking immediately add jello and food coloring. Place fresh strawberries in a baked 9-inch pie shell.
Pour the cooled glaze on top of strawberries.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cheesy o's
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Melt butter in baking pan.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Add cereal; mix well.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: minestrone
directions: Put all ingredients into pot, except cabbage, zucchini and beans.
Let cook 1 hour; add rest of ingredients.
Let simmer another 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: inside-out ravioli
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in large skillet.
Cook spinach, using package directions.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add water to make one cup.
Add spinach liquid and next 5 ingredients to meat mixture; simmer 10 minutes.

title: milk chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat and remove from stove. Add 2 cups sugar. Beat well. Mix in eggs and vanilla; blend well. Sift together flour, cocoa and salt. Add to sugar mixture. Mix well. Stir in coconut. Spread into greased 9 x 13 baking pan.

title: baked rice dressing
directions: Mix all in large bowl.
Bake in covered 9 x 13-inch bowl at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake just as listed.
Sprinkle cake mix over the whole top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook onions in melted margarine until limp.
Add thawed broccoli, salt, pepper and savory.
Cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Put spaghetti into greased 3-quart casserole.
Cover with a layer of cheese slices.
Pour in milk. Add a layer of broccoli, then cover with cheese slices.
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar well. Add eggs and beat. Sift dry ingredients together. Add this a little at a time while beating the egg mixture.
Add bananas and nuts. Bake in greased, slightly floured loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Makes one loaf.

title: *no crust coconut pie*
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add vanilla, then add milk and coconut.
Grease two 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: macaroni cheese salad with dill weed
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Turn, while still hot, into a bowl that contains butter and Parmesan cheese; toss to coat.
Add celery, cheese, salad cubes, mayonnaise to moisten, salt, pepper, seasoned salt and mustard;
mix well and chill.
Turn out on salad greens, and if desired, 2 cups of slivered ham or 1/4 cup of real bacon crumbs may be added to recipe.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: squash balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and form into small balls.
Roll in cornflakes.
Drop in hot grease and fry.

title: hamburger quiche(serves 4)
directions: Brown ground chuck; add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender; drain off fat.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Add beef, cheese and salt.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into uncooked pastry shell and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
It's ready when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Whip the cream cheese.
Stir in sour cream, then add sugar and vanilla; blend well.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put granulated sugar and cinnamon in bag.
Shake biscuits (quartered) in bag.
Layer biscuits in tube pan.
Pour extra sugar/cinnamon mixture over biscuits in pan.
In a saucepan, mix brown sugar and butter for 1 minute.
Pour mixture over biscuits as you layer them in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
To serve, dump out of pan onto plate.

title: pizzarino green beans
directions: Combine drained beans with remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring gently.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; let stand a while, preparing other ingredients.
Add the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, dates and nuts; mix.
Add the oil and vanilla; mix well.
Cook in tube pan or loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cranberry-raspberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
May be refrigerated, covered, for 1 month.
Makes 5 cups.

title: berniece thurn's pancake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Mix together yolks and the rest of ingredients; fold in egg whites.
Cook on hot griddle or heavy frying pan until bubbly on top; turn once.
Cook until golden brown.
Serve with hot syrup and butter.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; form into small meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes uncovered in baking dish.
Add tomatoes and peas. Return to oven for 15 to 20 minutes with cover on.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: noodles warsaw
directions: Chop cabbage into pieces.
Brown sausage, season with chili powder.
Drain sausage.
Bring water to a boil and cook noodles for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tootie fruitie salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, place peaches, pineapple and fruit cocktail if used with all juices; slice strawberries and add
to other fruit, then add pudding mixes. Do not prepare pudding, just dump in bowl with fruit and mix. Add bananas, sliced or chunk-sizes. Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: june's kidney beans(abington grange supper)
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Place salt pork in the bottom of a bean pot, drain the beans and to pot with all other ingredients.
Cover with hot water and bake at 325° for 5 or 6 hours.
Add more water as needed and reduce temperature to 300° for last hour.
Add more molasses, if desired.
Fork test, done when beans are tender, but not mushy.
Serves 10 hungry people.

title: melanie's simple sorbet
directions: Freeze unopened can of fruit for at
least 12 hours (longer is even better).
Dip frozen can in hot water a few seconds to loosen edges and make it easier to get out the contents.
Cut the frozen fruit up into chunks and put into food processor.
Add lemon juice, liqueur and cranberries. Pulse on/off for about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately or can be scooped into small balls and stored in freezer until ready to serve.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (or longer, if needed).

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into large chucks.
Put in casserole.
Brown ground chuck and onion; drain.
Add tomato soup (not diluted). Put over cabbage.
Cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stir in 1/2 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together beans, brown sugar, barbecue sauce and bacon. Saute onion and pepper; add to other mixture.
Put in baking dish; bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix all together, refrigerate overnight, drain and serve.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Beat eggs and add all ingredients, cooking constantly.
Chill! Fold in egg whites and cream; fold in brandy and rum.
Chill, then add vanilla.

title: honey drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and honey.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 350°.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Put all the ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix on low for 15 minutes.

title: white enchiladas
directions: Crush Doritos.
Mix together soup, sour cream, chilies, onion and chicken.
In a 3-quart casserole, layer Doritos, soup mixture and cheese in that order.
Make 2 layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Brown meat in a large saucepan and drain.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, mix Ricotta cheese or cottage cheese, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Put a little of the meat sauce in bottom of 13 x 9 baking dish and alternate layers as follows:
noodles, 1/3 meat sauce, half of cheese mixture.
Repeat and then top with remaining meat sauce.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for one hour or until noodles are tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: nanaimo bars
directions: Prepare 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable spray.
Cook margarine, sugar, chocolate and vanilla in top of double boiler over simmering water until blended.
Add egg; stir slowly.
Cook 5 minutes; stir constantly.
Add vanilla, cracker crumbs and pecans. Press into prepared pan.
Chill 15 minutes.
Cream margarine and Neufchatel cheese until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add powdered sugar; beat until smooth.
Add color; pour over cracker mixture.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Melt butter and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Spread over cream filling.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares (36).

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well, pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and broth and pour over chicken.
Place sliced boiled eggs over soup mixture.
Mix flour, margarine and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: spudnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Mix potatoes and milk.
Add flour salt, shortening and sugar.
Add 3 more cups flour and knead.
If needed, add 1 more cup flour.
Let dough double itself, then roll out and cut with regular doughnut cutter.
Let rise until twice their regular size.
Cook in deep oil at 390°.
Makes 4 dozen plus holes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Cook according to directions; drain.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly, except only add 1/2 cup of tomato ketchup at this time.
Mix with hands.
Pack firmly into ungreased baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
At the last 15 minutes of baking time, take the meat loaf out and brush the other 1/2 cup of tomato ketchup over the top.
Put back in oven for rest of baking time.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes in a preheated 425° oven.
Drain broth.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, basil or oregano and optional pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Pour heated sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes uncovered.

title: "momma's chili"
directions: Cook in at least a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Brown the ground chuck and chopped onion until the meat is thoroughly cooked.
Add the salt and pepper for seasoning.
Then add the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil over low heat for 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir often to avoid burning.
No lid is necessary.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Shape into 1-teaspoon size balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: strawberry-banana whip
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth. Chill or serve immediately.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Melt Crisco in small pan; blend in flour.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until very thick and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Pour into bowl and add onion, lemon juice and seasonings.
Stir in salmon. Shape into balls.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Combine egg with water. Dip balls in mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry until browned, about 3 minutes.
Serve plain or with cream gravy with peas.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with bread crumbs, egg, milk, onion, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Pack mixture lightly in a 2-quart loaf dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave 5 minutes at Medium-high.
Top with catsup.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes on High or until done.
Remove from microwave. Cover with aluminum foil and let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix sour cream, milk, Bisquick, eggs, pepper and salt together; stir in ham, cheese and chilies.
Pour into deep pie plate.
Cook until inserted knife comes out clean at 400° (40 minutes).
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Let rest about 5 minutes.

title: southern okra
directions: Cook okra in boiling salted water 10 minutes; drain.
Brown onion and green pepper in salad oil.
Add tomatoes and cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add okra and remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are just tender, stirring as little as possible.
One cup canned tomatoes may be used in place of fresh tomatoes.
Serves 4.

title: simple super fudge
directions: Use a double boiler; heat chocolate chips until melted.
Add can of condensed milk and vanilla.
(Also peanut butter if desired.)
Add nuts.
Pour into a lightly buttered 8-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Cool for 1 or more hours and then cut into squares.

title: wet chicken
directions: Wash and cut chicken.
Lightly salt and pepper, then place in flour.
Place shortening into frypan on medium heat.
Brown chicken and then place into a large pot with a lid.
After all chicken has been browned, pour remaining drippings over chicken and cover chicken with water.
Bring to a boil and then simmer 1 hour. Remove chicken.
It should have made its own gravy.
Pour over rice or potatoes.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash
and
drain
celery.
Cut into pieces three inches long. Fray
ends	if
you
want the celery to curl.
Chill in cold water
overnight.
Mix
and blend sour cream, mayonnaise and pecans.
Drain the crisp celery sticks and fill with this mixture.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Cut up celery, onion and bell pepper; add to sausage.
Pour in chicken broth.
Add uncooked rice.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
When cooked, fluff with fork.

title: lime-sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water for 24 hours.
Rinse in clear water several times.
Soak in clean water for 3 hours.
Drain. Mix the cloves, vinegar, celery seed, salt and mixed spices; pour over pickles.
Let stand overnight.
Heat to boiling and put into jars.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull berries; set aside.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and Jell-O.
Add water and syrup.
Cook over medium until thickened. Mixture won't be real thick.
Cool.
When cool, pour over berries and toss lightly.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Refrigerate until set, about 3 or 4 hours.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Serves 6.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt. Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Slowly add scalded milk and stir until well blended. Pour into unbaked, deep, 9-inch pie shell. Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: forget-me-not cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until foamy and white.
Add salt.
Continue to beat, gradually adding sugar until a stiff peak forms.
Fold in morsels and pecans.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet by the spoonful.
Place in oven and turn oven off.
Do not open door until the next morning.
Yields 40 to 60 cookies.

title: salmonettes heloise
directions: Pour salmon juice into measuring cup and set aside.
Put salmon in mixing bowl and 1 egg.
Break up salmon and mix the egg real good.
Fork in 1/2 cup flour.
Mixture is thick.
Add a little pepper, 1/4 salmon juice and add 1 teaspoon baking powder. Beat with a fork.
It must foam.
Pour into salmon mixture.
Mix with fork.
Scoop with small spoons into hot oil.
Makes brown tidbits.
Stick with toothpick and serve with dip or put a hot sauce over them.

title: german cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in one and one-half quarts of water until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook until cheese is melted.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, in saucepan and cook until it thickens.
Add vanilla.
This will get thicker as it cools.

title: double quick rolls(makes 1 dozen rolls)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a large bowl.
Add water, shortening and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Stir down batter by beating about 25 strokes.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin tins.
Let rise until batter rounds over tops of cups, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake until golden brown (15 to 20 minutes).

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes, gradually adding the sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Spread onto jelly roll pan; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Unroll onto toweling sprinkled with powdered sugar; spread filling mixture thick over roll.
Roll up and allow to cool; slice.

title: basic turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; place in lightly greased 4 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pan or shape in loaf form and place into 1-quart greased baking dish.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until meat is no longer pink in center of loaf. Unmold on platter; top with sliced tomatoes and garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: bisquick butter biscuits
directions: Cut cold butter into 1/4-inch pieces.
Toss baking mix and butter with fork until coated.
Add milk; stir just until milk is absorbed (do not overstir).

title: microwave sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough or just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in microwave dish.
Sprinkle with melted butter and herbs.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes; rearrange after 5 minutes.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave for 4 to 6 minutes until potatoes are soft and cheese melted.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: chocolate coconut drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate in 2-quart saucepan over low heat; stir frequently until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut, walnuts and milk.

title: stir-fried pork with garlic
directions: In a bowl, combine pork, sherry, soy sauce, vinegar, cornstarch, ginger, sugar and chili paste.
Toss to mix.
Marinate 30 minutes.

title: baked pineapple(side dish for ham)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be served with ham.

title: ribbon jello salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 4 tablespoons cold water.
Set aside 1/2 cup of mixture.
Put in 1/3 cup sour cream.
Pour remaining in a 9 x 12-inch glass pan.
Set until firm, at least 1/2 hour.
Pour on sour cream mixture; set 1/2 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs and bananas. Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Put in bottom of an 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Cook celery and onion; drain peas.
Spread celery, onion and peas over meat.
Spread undiluted mushroom soup over all. Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake in a 350° oven 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: mandarin pork chops with wild rice
directions: In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil and brown chops.
Add water, long grain and wild rice with sauce (original recipe), reserved syrup and green onions.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 13 minutes or until pork is done.
Stir in oranges; heat through.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half.
Fill 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with pineapple and bananas and the prepared pudding mix.
Last, top with Cool Whip.
Chill 30 minutes before serving.

title: red beans
directions: Add all ingredients together with enough water to cook until tender and of desired consistency.

title: caramel corn
directions: Prepare popcorn and add peanuts, if desired, or any kind of nuts you want.
Cook sugar, butter, salt and Karo for 5 minutes. Take from stove and add baking soda.
It will foam, then add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Spread out onto 2 cookie sheets and bake in 250° oven for 1/2 hour.
Stir after 15 minutes. Pour onto wax paper and spread apart.
Cool and then it can be stored in plastic bags or an airtight container.
It will last a while.
Yield:
8 quarts.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Put all in mixer with cake mix and follow directions on box of cake mix.

title: rice krispies raisin cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and soda; set aside.
In mixer bowl thoroughly combine sugar, brown sugar and margarine. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add Rice Krispies and raisins, mixing until it combines.
Drop cookies on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 16 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Layer on platter in this order:
Spread bean dip on a large, shallow serving platter.
Peel, pit and mash avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; mix in separate bowl.
Layer avocado mixture over bean dip, then layer taco seasoning mixture over avocado layer.
Top with green onions, tomatoes and sliced black olives, then sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top of dip mixture.
Serve with large, round tortilla chips.

title: strombolis
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons oil with garlic. Add tomatoes.
Drain all liquid so mixture is very dry.
Flatten out crescent rolls into 1 sheet, mush seams together so there are no holes.
Place meat and vegetable mixture on one half and bring other side over.
Press edges together.
Cook 35 minutes at 350° until crust is golden brown.
Serves 2 adults and 1 to 2 children. Repeat recipe to make more Strombolis as needed.

title: sauerkraut and spareribs
directions: Rinse kraut and put in roaster.
Top kraut with onion slices and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Add water so it is almost to the top of the kraut in the pan.
Brown ribs in skillet and lay on top of kraut.
Mix in a large measuring cup ketchup and Worcestershire sauce, and then fill the cup with water so the mixture measures a total of 1 cup.
Mix and pour over ribs and kraut.
Put in oven for 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat egg in large bowl until thickened.
Add marmalade and butter until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine buttermilk and lemon juice. Alternately add dry and liquid ingredients in thirds to egg mixture, stirring until well mixed.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix with sugar.
Cut in butter; add beaten egg and mix to make crumbs.
Place 1/2 of crumbs in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Distribute cherries evenly and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or other topping. Sprinkle crumbs lightly with cinnamon.

title: garlic buttered green beans
directions: Cook green beans in water, covered, until tender.
Meanwhile, in a skillet saute mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add onion powder and garlic powder.
Drain beans.
Add to skillet and toss. Season with salt and pepper.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: mother's golden potato casserole
directions: Grate potatoes coarsely.
Add other ingredients, except last 2, mix thoroughly.
Press into casserole dish.
Top with mixture of bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese and apple pancakes
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Combine all other ingredients in a medium size bowl and mix well. Fold in egg whites.
Heat oil or melt butter in a skillet.
When it is hot enough to sizzle a drop of batter on contact, add spoonfuls of batter.
Fry on both sides until firm and lightly browned. Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together first 7 ingredients, all into a large mixing bowl.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Beat together until smooth.
Add last 2 ingredients.

title: easy spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and bell pepper.
Drain grease.
Add spaghetti and tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Drain juice off strawberries and pineapple; add enough water to make 3 1/2 cups juice.
Heat liquid and pour over Jell-O to dissolve.
Stir well and jell slightly.
Mash bananas and add strawberries, pineapple and pecans.
Fold into Jell-O mixture and pour half of mixture into mold.
Spread on sour cream.
Add remaining half of mixture and chill.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pie filling.
Turn into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Beat together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Gradually add lemon Jell-O.
Stir in undrained pineapple and whip 1/2 cup whipping cream.
Fold into lemon mixture with one cup of tiny marshmallows. Spread on top of cherry layer.
Top with nuts.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken pineapple salad
directions: Remove giblets and neck from chicken, then rinse chicken well under cold water.
Place chicken, breast side down, in an 8-quart kettle.
Add carrots, cut up celery, onion, 1 teaspoon salt, the bay leaf and 1 quart of water.
Bring to boiling over high heat. Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for about 2 hours, or until chicken is tender.
Let stand, uncovered, and frequently spoon broth over chicken for 1 hour, or until cool enough to handle.
Remove meat from bones in as large of pieces as you can.
Pull skin from chicken.
Cut chicken into 1/2 to 1-inch chunks.
Chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan and spread frozen potatoes in pan. Saute onion (chopped) in 1/4 cup margarine.
Mix together onion, creamed soup, sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix together corn flake crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Pour on top of casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot cross buns(a family tradition on good friday)
directions: Combine sugar, salt, yeast and flour in large bowl.
In 1-quart saucepan, over low heat, heat milk and butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
With mixer at low speed, beat liquid into dry ingredients until blended.
Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes.
Beat in egg and 1 cup flour to make a thick batter; continue beating 2 minutes, scraping bowl often.
Stir in raisins and flour to make a soft dough.

title: picante sauce
directions: Put tomatoes, onions, bell peppers and jalapeno peppers through food grinder.
Add seasonings and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring often.
Pour in pint jars and seal in hot water bath.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat egg; add sugar and salt. Mix baking powder in the flour. Mix soda in buttermilk. Then pour into egg and sugar. Add butter and stir until mixed well. Add all to flour. Mix well; add flour until stiff dough. Roll real thin and sprinkle with sugar. Cut and cook in moderate oven until brown through. Makes 150 cookies.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Make jello with 1 cup of water; let cool.
Cream the cream cheese and add jello.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.
(I use a ring mold.)
Serves 10 to 12.

title: white greek cookies
directions: Cream butter well, then add sugar gradually.
Add egg yolks and vanilla, continuing to mix.
Fold in almonds and whiskey.

Add flour and baking powder and mix by hand until dough is formed. Then make small shaped cookies (round balls, flat half moons). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (almost light gold) on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool cookies before sifting confectioners sugar on top and bottom.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Cut Spam and cheese in pieces.
Use food grinder with small attachments.
Grind all and add enough Miracle Whip to moisten well.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Sift flour in a large bowl.
Make hole in center of flour and put in all ingredients in the hole.
Work up as you would for biscuits.
When all is mixed together, roll out on floured paper and cut.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Follow directions on cake package mix.
In a separate bowl, mix remainder of ingredients.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour cake mix into pan.
Pour Ricotta mixture over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or 325° if oven is too hot.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: cherry tomato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Combine bacon with tomatoes, cucumber and onions.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, sweet basil and pepper.
Mix well and chill.
Combine vinegar and salad oil; shake well.
Just before serving, pour over salad and toss.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seedless raisin tarts
directions: Beat all ingredients together and fill unbaked tart shells. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Makes about 15.
Bake at 350°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and sugar; add eggs and flavoring.
Sift flour, cinnamon and nutmeg and add a little at a time.
Beat well; add nuts and fruit.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.
Take out of oven.
Put cherries, pineapple and pecans on top.
Cook 1/2 hour longer.

title: orange blossom cream
directions: Dissolve sugar in orange juice.
Whip evaporated milk until stiff.
Combine with juice; mix well.
Serve immediately.

title: independent dream cake
directions: Gradually add orange juice to confectioners sugar, blending well.
Makes 1/3 cup.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a greased casserole dish.
Top with Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut logs
directions: Mix
well peanut butter, Rice Krispies, oleo and sugar. Melt chocolate chips and wax.
Roll by teaspoon size in hands. Keep your
fingers
wet
and
then
dip the logs in chocolate mixture. Put on wax paper.

title: bread-n-butter pudding
directions: Butter glass baking dish.
Cut buttered bread into triangles; mix fruit with sugar.
Arrange buttered bread, fruit and sugar in layers in the dish.
Beat the eggs with the milk, then pour egg and milk mixture over the bread-butter-fruit and allow this to soak in for 15 to 20 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until custard is set and top is lightly browned.

title: peanut butter bar cookies
directions: Melt together corn syrup and white sugar.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Add 7 cups cereal (corn flakes, Rice Krispies, Cheerios, etc.).
Mix well.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pecan dainties
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar. Blend in flour and vanilla. Stir in nuts.
Using about 1 teaspoon of dough, shape into crescents or balls.
