Place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° until lightly browned. Cool. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: mexican white corn
directions: Melt the margarine and cream cheese over low heat.
Leave all liquid on chilies for spicier flavor.
Mix altogether.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrots a l'orange
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar in small saucepan.
Pour in orange juice and mix well.
Heat, stirring until thickened.
Stir in butter and ginger.
Pour over cooked carrots.

title: tomatoes with mozzarella
directions: Layer slices of tomatoes and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with chopped fresh basil, salt and freshly ground pepper.
Drizzle with extra virgin olive oil.

title: eggplant supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Fry eggplant and drain on paper towels. Cook spinach according to directions and drain.
Mix Ricotta cheese and spincah, don't beat, just blend.
Spread evenly in pan. Layer eggplant on top.
Either slice or grate Mozzarella cheese and layer over eggplant.
Cover with sauce.
Sprinkle grated cheese. Give it a blessing and throw it in preheated oven for 45 minutes until bubbly.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in buttered casserole. Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mandarin and pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice and add to water to make 3 cups; boil.
Add Jell-O, fruit and cinnamon.
Let set, serves 8.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Mix nuts, sugar, flour and butter; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel and cut tomatoes in 8 pieces.
Put onions and peppers through grinder.
Put all ingredients in large pot and cook until thick.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: cherries in snow
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix in powdered sugar, vanilla and milk. Gently fold in Cool Whip.
In glass bowl, put some of the cake cubes.
Drizzle some of the Cool Whip mixture over cake.
Spoon pie filling over that.
Add another layer of cake, Cool Whip and cherries.
Keep making layers until all ingredients are used up, ending with cherries on top.
Store in refrigerator or make ahead of time and freeze.
This makes a lot!

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Cook tortellini to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain; rinse with cold water.
In large clear glass bowl with straight sides or 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer cabbage, spinach, tortellini, tomatoes and green onions.
Pour dressing evenly over top; sprinkle with bacon.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time. Makes 8 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: pasta
directions: Cook the pasta in boiling water (do not overcook); drain in colander.
Pour warm pasta in bowl and pour Wish-Bone dressing over.
Stir.
Cool at room temperature.
Meanwhile, dice green peppers and thinly slice onions.
Cube the cheese into 1/4-inch cubes.
Add all to pasta except cheese and parsley.
They can be added just before serving.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: lou's turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in dish.
Cover with potato chips, crushed or uncrushed.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Great for after the holiday meals.

title: mediterranean vegetable pie(yields 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place eggplant between several thicknesses of paper towels.
Sprinkle with a teaspoon of salt; weigh down with breadboard or several recipe books and let stand 30 minutes.
Cut into 1/4-inch cubes.
Heat 1/2 cup olive oil in a large Teflon skillet; add the eggplant and quickly toss to coat with oil.
Cook, stirring constantly, until eggplant is tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove to a large bowl.
Pour remaining olive oil in the skillet, add onion, green pepper, zucchini and garlic.
Cook until veggies are tender, but do not lose their shape, about 5 minutes.
Reserve.
Combine oregano, basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper in a small measuring cup.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Heat raisins and water just until the mixture comes to a boil. Cool.
Add soda and set aside.
Mix sugar, oleo and eggs and beat until smooth.
Add flour, salt, raisins and water.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° until, when tested, the toothpick comes out clean.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In large bowl, mix first 6 ingredients.
In a jar or small bowl, combine sugar and oil.
Pour over vegetables and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.

title: chinese country ribs
directions: Combine soy sauce, marmalade, catsup and garlic.
Brush both sides of ribs.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour in remaining sauce. Cover and cook on low, 8 to 10 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan crisp treats
directions: Melt margarine for 1 minute in microwave.
Add sugar and microwave 2 more minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Grease jelly roll cookie sheet.
Carefully break each cracker into 4 pieces and place side by side in a single layer on cookie sheet.
Drizzle pecan mixture over crackers.
(Do 1 pan at a time.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan while still warm.

title: hamburger pizza
directions: Prepare pizza dough according to package directions.
Mix together tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Add dash of oregano and dash of garlic salt. Spread sauce over unbaked pizza crust. Spread browned ground chuck over the sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake on lowest rack for 10 minutes at 500° or
until golden brown.
Makes 1 pizza.

title: mother's cornbread dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in part of broth until tender, then puree.
Crumble cornbread and toasted bread.
Mix with rice, pureed onion mixture and enough broth to make a fairly soupy mixture.
Heat bacon grease in shallow baking pan and add dressing mixture and bake at 400° until brown on top and crusty on edges.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut skinned and boneless chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces.
Mix slightly beaten egg white, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, soy sauce and fresh ground pepper in a plastic bag.
Add chicken, tie bag and refrigerate for up to 1 hour, turning bag occasionally. Cut both peppers into thin strips.
Slice onion very thin and separate into rings.
Mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch, water, sugar and sesame oil.
Heat wok until very hot, pour oil down sides of wok and rotate to oil all sides.
Add onion, garlic and ginger. Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes, until onion is light brown and softened. Add chicken and stir-fry until chicken pieces turn white.
Add hoisin sauce and chili paste; stir for about 30 to 40 seconds. Stir in broth and heat to boiling.
Add the green and red pepper strips; stir-fry for about 1 minute more.
Add the cornstarch mixture and stir until thickened.
If desired, sprinkle with roasted peanuts.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 9 g, protein 23 g, fat 17 g, calories 284.

title: persimmon marmalade
directions: Cut, core and mash fruit.
Add other ingredients and cook until thick. Pour into jars and process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 6 (1/2-pint) jars.

title: pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt together. Then add to egg yolk and milk mixture. stir into heated milk. Cook over medium heat until thick stirring constantly. Add butter, vanilla and coconut, banana or cocoa. Pour into baked 9 inch pie shell.

title: crispy chocolate log
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 2-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper; grease the paper and set aside.
In a large microwave-safe bowl, combine marshmallows, butter and peanut butter.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir until well blended.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
Spread into prepared pan.
In a microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate and butterscotch chips. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 2 minutes.
Stir; spread over cereal to within 1-inch of edges.
Roll up jelly roll style, starting with a short side, peeling away waxed paper while rolling.
Place, seam side down, on a serving plate.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until set.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Makes 10 servings.

title: oven baked halibut a la orange
directions: Line a 12 x 8 x 2-inch shallow baking dish with foil.
Lightly brush both sides of halibut steaks with oil.

Arrange in dish. Sprinkle with orange peel and dill. Cover dish with foil and bake at 450°, allowing 10 to 12 minutes cooking time per inch of thickness measured at its thickest part or until halibut flakes when tested with a fork.

title: pocket sandwiches
directions: Take
biscuit
and roll flat.
Top with a filling of your choice.
Take
another
biscuit
and
roll flat;
cover. Take a fork and crimp edges.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes or until done.

title: shakertown corn pudding
directions: In a large bowl, blend butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add the eggs and beat well with a rotary beater or mixer on low.
Stir in the corn and milk.
(If using frozen corn, chop it up a little first to release the milky juices.)

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken in oil.
Sprinkle with salt; add vegetables and broth.
Bring to full boil over medium heat.
Separate vegetables with fork, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Combine sour cream, flour, and paprika.
Stir into vegetables and heat gently.

title: potato and ham chowder
directions: Potatoes may be red skinned or other thin skinned; cut in 1/2-inch chunks.
Ham is fully cooked, smoked and cut in small chunks.
Corn may be fresh, canned or frozen.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine beans; toss all together.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, toss to marinate beans and drain.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Put your cream cheese in a large bowl.
Chop up your ham in a processor.
Pour your ham in another bowl.
Chop green onions in food processor.
Mix together.
Put about 5 or 6 handfuls of chopped ham in the cream cheese and onion mixture.
Add Accent. Roll into 2 balls, then roll in ham that is left over.
Serve with crackers.

title: carrot pineapple bread
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients; add remaining ingredients and blend.
It's much easier to use Cusinart or blender for carrots.
Lightly grease 2 loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning per package directions and simmer approximately 5 minutes.
Layer beef on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish; top with refried beans; layer sour cream and salsa to taste and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts (approximately 10 minutes).
Garnish with diced lettuce, tomato, onion and black olives.
Add salsa and serve with tortilla chips.
Enjoy!

title: heath bars
directions: Line crackers on bottom of cookie sheet.
Boil butter and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour sugar and butter mixture over crackers.
Bake 4 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Let melt.
Spread with butter knife.
Put in refrigerator for about 10 minutes.
Remove and cut into squares.
Return to refrigerator.
Sprinkle nuts on top, if you desire.

title: sausage snack wraps
directions: Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each triangle lengthwise into thirds.
Place sausages on shortest side of each triangle. Roll up from shortest side to the opposite point.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.
May be prepared ahead and refrigerated up to 2 hours.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Melt cheese and stir in other ingredients.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Serve with plain tortilla chips.

title: nannie's apple-cranberry casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in baking dish, then make topping.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Use a casserole dish with a cover.
Spray dish with Pam. Alternate bread slices and cheese slices.
(I also put mushrooms and chilies on top of cheese.)
Pour melted butter over this. Beat eggs well.
Add salt, pepper, mustard, milk, picante sauce, chilies and mushrooms.
Pour this mixture over bread and cheese. Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours.
(Can be made ahead and refrigerated for 2 days prior to baking.)
Cook covered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or 12 cup Bundt pan.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and flavorings.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool about 15 minutes in pan.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Wash vegetables; slice and remove seeds from peppers.
Cook until celery is tender, then press through a fine sieve or pureeing device.
Boil rapidly for about 30 minutes to evaporate some of the liquid.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture is thickened.
Fill hot, sterilized jars and seal at once.
This makes 3 to 4 pints of ketchup.

title: cucumber pickle relish
directions: Mix by hand and put in jars.
Makes 2 quarts.
Cover with lids (not sealed) and tighten and then loosen a little.
Pickles will work a little so it needs a little "working" space!
Refrigerate. Will keep up to a year.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Melt shortening in a large kettle.
Add meat and onion.
Brown slowly, stirring with a fork to break up meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except apples and pecans, mix well. Fold in fruit and nuts. Bake in well greased tube or bundt pan at 350 degrees for approximately 55 minutes.
Cool in pan. May serve with whipped cream.

title: wedding punch
directions: Freeze pineapple juice. Take out 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving time and partially thaw. Put in a large container and mash up. Add lemonade and orange juice, mixed with water as directed on cans. Add ginger ale. Stir and serve.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all together and let set for about 1 hour.

title: turkey alfredo casserole
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Run water over broccoli to thaw.

title: meat, potato, egg scramble
directions: Cook hash browns according to directions.
Beat desired amount of eggs with 2 teaspoons water, then pour over potatoes.
Cook eggs, turning 1 to 3 times.
When eggs are done, put cheese on top.
Cover pan to melt cheese.
Cook in 12 x 14-inch skillet. Five eggs will serve 4 people, 4 to 6 ounce portions.

title: cracked wheat cereal(diabetic approved)
directions: Toast cracked wheat and coconut by stirring constantly in a dry pan over medium heat for several minutes, until lightly browned.
Place in a saucepan andd remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped nut, if desired.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in
a saucepan and simmer on low for about 20 to 30 minutes. Store in refrigerator.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Layer peeled and sliced potatoes in a 9-inch pan. Mix margarine, flour, brown sugar and water.
Make a hot syrup and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Mix thoroughly and bake 16 to 20 minutes at 375° in a 10 x 14-inch pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: tender roast
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Slice onion in bottom of pan.
Wash; salt and pepper the roast.
Lay roast on onion in pan.
Cover roast with the undiluted soup.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Cook in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
This will make its own gravy.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in jars.
To each quart jar add 1/2 bunch dill or more, 1 garlic button and 1 small onion.
Let vinegar, water and salt come to a boil; pour over cucumbers. Seal.

title: orange supreme tropical delight cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box for making 2 (9-inch) round cakes.

title: pear butter
directions: Combine pears and water in a large Dutch oven.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat 40 minutes or until pears are soft, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Press pears through a sieve or food mill; measure 1 quart of puree.
Combine 1 quart puree with remaining ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, 15 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat; skim off foam.
Quickly pour hot pear mixture into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Yield:
2 pints.

title: eisenhower fudge
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients for 6 minutes (sugar, salt, butter and evaporated milk). Bring to a boil. Keep at a rolling boil over medium heat. Do not stir. Have a metal or glass bowl ready with the chocolate chips, chocolate squares and Fluff. Pour boiling syrup over this and stir until chocolate is melted. Stir in vanilla and nuts. Pour into buttered 9 x 13 pan. Cool slightly, then place in refrigerator to chill and become firm. Cut into squares with sharp knife.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, flour and meal.
Add beaten eggs, add other ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees until it does not shake.

title: julienne of beets and carrots or carrots and parsnips
directions: Cook beets.
Slip off skins and julienne.
Julienne carrots or parsnips. Cook to desired tenderness.
Melt butter and add to it a little orange juice.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add enough hot water to dry ingredients to wet it.
Add egg yolks, milk, margarine (melted) and flavoring.
Pour into uncooked pie crust and cook until firm, approximately 45 minutes.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, blend pepperoni, cheeses, oregano and egg.
Roll apart crescent rolls into 8 rectangles (press perforations to seal).
Spread mixture on each rectangle, making sure to cover to the edges.
Starting at shorter side, roll up and seal.
Cut each roll into 6 pieces.

title: finger paint
directions: Add boiling water to the starch and boil until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in the soap; add food coloring.

title: tank's taco grande(mom or dad will help with hard parts.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Spray Pam on bottom and sides of 9 x 13 baking dish. Cook turkey or beef until no longer pink, breaking up chunks to small crumbs. Add taco mix and water (see mix directions). Remove from heat. Add 1 cup of salsa.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place skinned chicken breasts in 8-inch square baking dish that has been lightly oiled.
Lightly salt and pepper.
Place drained sauerkraut over chicken; top with cheese slices, one over each breast.
Pour dressing evenly over the cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in a 325° oven about 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Makes four servings.
Baked potato skins can also be baked at the same time.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in a 2 x 8 x 12-inch dish, mixing well.
Layer with remaining ingredients in order listed.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: columbus cooler punch
directions: Mix all juices except 7-Up or ginger ale.
Add just before serving.

title: squash carrot casserole
directions: Cook squash according to directions on the package; drain. Sliver raw carrots on coarse side of grader.
Mix squash, carrots, pimentos, sour cream and undiluted soup in saucepan.
In separate bowl mix herb stuffing and margarine.
Line baking dish with half of herb stuffing mixture.
Pour in squash mixture and top with remaining half of herb stuffing mixture. Salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic; drain.
Add undrained tomatoes, sauce, paste, undrained mushrooms, water and all spices.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and add cooked noodles.

title: hearty lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils and let soak overnight; drain. Saute onions, celery and garlic in olive oil. Put soaked lentils in large pot and fill with 2 quarts water. Add sauteed vegetables, carrots, tomatoes (chopped very coarsely) along with all the puree, oregano, salt, pepper, parsley and bay leaf.

title: oatmeal walnut raisin cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and walnuts.
Drop from a tablespoon 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.

title: cherry confetti cake
directions: Sift or mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream the shortening and confectioners sugar.
Blend in the almond extract and eggs.
Measure milk and add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
(Begin and end with dry.)
Fold in walnuts and cherries.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Cut gently through batter to break air bubbles. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Remove from oven and while still warm spread on top with butter and sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Combine seasonings with flour.
Let margarine soften, mix in cheese and flour.
If using an electric mixer, blend in flour on mixing speed.
Mix the Rice Krispies in by hand.
Place ball the size of marble on ungreased baking sheet and press with a fork (dipped in flour) to flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove and let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend all together with hands until well blended.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar and curry powder.
Bring to a boil.
Drain the fruit and arrange in a 2-quart baking dish (about 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch).
Pour hot sauce over it. Garnish with cherries. Bake at 325° until it bubbles (about 30 to 40 minutes). Serve hot.
Very good with poultry, ham and pork.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: microwaved bread pudding
directions: In a 2-cup casserole, slightly beat eggs.
Add sugar and blend.
Pour in milk and blend with salt and cinnamon.
Add raisins and bread cubes.
Dot with butter.

title: 12-hour cole slaw
directions: Layer half of cabbage, onions and green pepper.
Sprinkle half of sugar over vegetables.
Repeat.
Let stand while making dressing.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add vinegar and water from beets. Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add beets and simmer 30 minutes.
When ready to serve, bring to a boil and add butter. Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.
Makes a large bowl.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Grind cranberries in blender.
Add marshmallows and sugar. Chill, covered, overnight.
Add grapes, apples, walnuts and salt. Fold in chilled, whipped cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and rinse with cold water several times.
Let drain.
Mix other ingredients in a large container.
Pour in beans and mix.
Let stand in the refrigerator 12 to 18 hours.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with Triscuits crackers or corn chips.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk, starting and ending with flour.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: summer succotash
directions: Cook corn and lima beans in a small amount of boiling water for 12 minutes or until tender; drain and set aside.
Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute chopped onion in bacon drippings until onion is tender; remove onion and set aside. Add flour to bacon drippings, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes and rest of ingredients.
Heat through.

title: grasshopper cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 4 ingredients and beat until stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil-covered cookie sheets.
Turn oven off and leave cookies in oven overnight.
Store in tins between wax paper.
May be frozen.

title: ann's beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.

title: nut cups
directions: Mix flour, margarine and cream cheese and refrigerate.
Mix brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and margarine.
Cook over low heat.
Watch closely as it burns easily.
Add walnuts.
Roll out dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with a scalloped cookie cutter.
Press into 1-inch muffin tin.
Drop 1 teaspoon of filling into each cup about 3/4 full.
They will swell.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Avoid overbrowning.

title: ribbon mold salad
directions: Mix together 3 cups of hot water, pineapple juice and lemon Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour mixture in pan and refrigerate to cool, but not set firm, about 1 hour.
Mix together lime Jell-O and 1.5 quarts of hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour lime Jell-O mixture into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan; chill until firmly set. Mix together strawberry Jell-O and 1.5 quarts of hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Allow mixture to cool.
In a small mixing bowl, cream the cream cheese.
Add whipped cream.
To this mixture, add the cooled lemon Jell-O mix and whip until blended thoroughly. Pour the lemon mixture on top of the set lime Jell-O.
Refrigerate until firm.
Pour strawberry Jell-O on top of the lemon mixture and let set again, until firm.

title: fresh tomato sauce for pasta or pizza crust, etc.
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook 10 minutes or until reduced to 4 cups.
Keep in freezer for quick pasta dishes.

title: chicken nest
directions: Arrange pasta in skillet.
Top with chicken (undrained), frozen peas, carrots and sliced onion.
Pour on broth.
Sprinkle with tarragon.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: gail's quiche lorraine
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Cook in 375° oven for about 1 hour.

title: mile a minute cupcakes(1942 recipe)
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Add flour, sifted with salt, baking powder, soda and cocoa alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add coffee; mix well.
Fill greased cupcake pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine and stir in pretzels and sugar.
Press gently into a 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes (do not overbake). Cool.

title: tammy's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions. Add eagle brand milk. Put in refrigerator for 5 to 10 minutes until set. While waiting for mixture to set, beat heavy whipping cream (use a mixer) until a soft peek. Fold in to pudding mixture. Start layering in a 2 qt. dish; putting pudding mixture first, then cookies and bananas. Refrigerate overnight so cookies get soft.

title: mama's bread pudding
directions: Scald milk with margarine.
Add with all remaining ingredients to bread and stir lightly.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add sugar.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with Marshmallow Creme while hot.
Cool 30 minutes and ice.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Beat lemonade concentrate in large bowl about 30 seconds. Gradually spoon in ice cream, blending well.
Gently stir whipped topping until smooth.
Freeze, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze at least 4 hours or until firm. Let stand at room temperature or in refrigerator about 30 minutes or until pie can be easily cut.
Garnish with strawberries.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Core the apples and peel them if you like.
(We prefer the added texture of the peels, but peeled apples look more sophisticated.)
Cut the apples crosswise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Melt about 2 tablespoons of the butter in a skillet and add a single layer of apple slices.
Raise the heat and saute the slices, turning occasionally, until browned, about 5 minutes. With a slotted spoon, transfer apples to a bowl.
Repeat with more butter and another batch of apples until all have been cooked.

title: hamburger stuffed bread
directions: Cut off top of loaf of bread and hollow out, forming a crust shell.
Tear enough bread for 2 cups; set aside.
Brown beef and oil; add green pepper, Worcestershire sauce and cheese soup. Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Fill in bread crust. Place American cheese slices diagonally on top.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the cream of mushroom soup and milk together.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and place in fridge overnight (12 hours).
Before baking, sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Grease the pan before adding ingredients.

title: ruth's crab pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1/2 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce and a little lemon juice.
Spread in bottom of pie plate.
Pick shells from large can of backfin crabmeat.
Spread over cream cheese. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix Heinz chili sauce, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire, horseradish and lemon juice and pour over crab. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into a 10 x 14-inch pan. Top with cheese crackers and melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Set aside to drain.
Put veggies in skillet with small amount of oil.
Stir fry.
Add 3 tablespoons soy sauce.
Add rice.
Stir fry until hot.
Ready to eat.

title: frozen passion
directions: Ice Cream Maker Method:
Mix and pour into ice cream freezer container.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix 1 cup of flour, baking powder and butter; add egg and milk.
Mix.
Press into greased pie pan.
Arrange rhubarb in pie shell
Sprinkle with Jell-O.

title: rolls with gold medal flour
directions: Mix
all with flour.
May have to add a little more flour but make a soft dough.
Knead real good.
Put in a greased bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk, about
1 hour.
Work down and make into rolls.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: applesauce jello salad
directions: Add cup of boiling water to package of jello.
Mix until dissolved.
Add package of frozen berries; stir until thawed.
Add the applesauce and stir well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill in refrigerator until set.
For the topping, fold in 1 cup of marshmallows into 1 cup of sour cream or Cool Whip and spread over the set jello.

title: pasta alfredo
directions: Heat butter and cream.
Do not boil.
Mound pasta in warm buttered bowl and pour on cream; sprinkle generously with cheese and toss thoroughly but lightly.
Season to taste.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In 2-quart saucepan stir together 1 cup sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks. Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in next 3 ingredients, cool. Turn into pastry shell.
In small bowl with mixer at high speed beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar; continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread some meringue around edge of filling first, touching crust all around, then fill in center.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix all together. Put in pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: lasagna
directions: Two days before using, make sauce:
Brown onions in bottom of a large Dutch oven.
Add meat and brown.
Stir occasionally to break it up well.
Add salt, pepper, lots of oregano, garlic powder, 3 cans of tomato paste and can of puree.
Add 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Cover.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring every 30 minutes or so and taste to season.
When done, put in a large airtight container.
Store in refrigerator at least 24 hours before using.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and egg. Then add pumpkin and vanilla. Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt. Add walnuts. Drop with spoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for almost 12 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook corn, tomatoes, carrots and butter beans.
Mix all ingredients and heat good.
Put in jars and seal.
Cook in pressure canner at 10 pounds for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in water with onion.
Remove chicken; drain and set onions aside.
Chop chicken; salt and pepper to taste. Combine chicken, onion and mayonnaise to taste.
Add celery, lemon juice, pimento, eggs and soup.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with almonds, potato chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cheese grits
directions: While grits are still hot, add cheeses and margarine.
Allow to cool; add eggs and milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
This dish can be made ahead of time, frozen and reheated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Sift and measure the flour.
Cut the butter into the flour. Break the egg into a measuring cup, then add enough water to come up to the 3/4 cup line.
Add to the flour; mix lightly with a fork. Drop by tablespoonfuls over boiling meat and broth or into well-greased steamer placed over boiling water.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes, or until dumplings are tender.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until cake is done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Dust apples, raisins and nuts with some of the flour; set aside.
Blend oil, sugar and slightly beaten eggs; set aside. Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to egg mixture and add vanilla.
Fold in coated apples, nuts and raisins; pour into a 10-inch greased tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheerios nuggets
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Grease two 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until bubbly around edges.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda until foamy and light colored. Pour over cereal, peanuts and raisins in greased 4-quart bowl. Stir until mixture is coated.
Spread evenly in pans.
Bake 15 minutes.
Stir.
Let stand just until cool, about 10 minutes. Loosen mixture with metal spatula.
Let stand until firm, about 30 minutes.
Break into bite size pieces.
Makes about 10 cups of snack.

title: lime salad chiffon with graham crackers
directions: Make the crust with butter and cracker crumbs.
Put into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: slushy punch
directions: Mix jello and sugar with 3 cups boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in freezer.
Stir after about 3 hours and every hour thereafter until it is slushy.

title: harry potter punch
directions: Dissolve jello into boiling water. Add sugar and dissolve. Add cold water, pineapple juice and lemon juice. Pour into clean milk or apple juice jugs and chill well or start to freeze.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Beat eggs and mix with flour, salt, cinnamon, soda, vanilla, nuts, sugar, oil, bananas (not mashed) and pineapple.
Do not beat.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: toffee candy
directions: Cook butter and sugar on medium heat, stirring frequently, until temperature reaches 290° on candy thermometer.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet with sides.
Spread out.

title: oven barbecue sauce
directions: Mix the tomato soup, brown sugar and vinegar together well. Bake meat until it has about 20 minutes left. Pour the barbecue sauce on the meat and continue to bake uncovered until the meat is done. This is great on pork chops, some cuts of beef and a great way to dress up leftover meat.

title: st. timothy's coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Sift together, flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add nuts and raisins to dry ingredients.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture on top before baking.
Sprinkle on bottom after baking.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, spices, salt, baking powder, and soda together. Cream sugar and oil together while adding one egg at a time. Begin to add flour mixture, zucchini, apple sauce, pineapple, raisins, and nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.
Makes three loaves. Really, really good!

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Fill each tortilla with 2 tablespoons of mixture, 1 tablespoon of each cheese and top with onion.
Roll and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put remaining meat mixture over top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt butter in a large sauce pan and add all ingredients, except shrimp. Cook over medium heat for approximately 5 minutes. Add shrimp and saute for 4 minutes on each side.
Remove from heat and
ladle butter sauce over shrimp.
Garnish
with fresh parsley and 3 slices of lemon.
Serves two.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Take 1 can of beans; drain 1/2 water; put in casserole dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup, then onions and cheese; mix well.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes or until onions and green beans are tender.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a saucepan, make a roux with flour and butter.
Add mustard.
Lower heat and add one-half of the milk, stirring so as not to scald.
In a pot, cook pasta until it's half done.
Saute onion and add to roux mixture along with cheeses and rest of milk.

title: paintbrush cookies
directions: Give each child 3 large marshmallows and toothpick.
Instruct to insert toothpick and to align marshmallows.
Decorate snowmen with raisins, fruit slices and cereal pieces.
Eat as snack.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Slowly cook oil, onions, celery, salt and beef, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes and tomatoes; stir well. Place in casserole dish. Place strips of pastry on top.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well and add Hershey's syrup.
Mix together flour, soda and salt. Melt Hershey bars; alternately add buttermilk, Hershey bars and vanilla.
Bake in stem pan at 350° for one hour.

title: baked beans with green pepper and carrots
directions: Wash beans, cover with water and cook until soft.
Drain, not too dry.
Add salt and bacon drippings.
Mix in baking dish the beans, brown sugar, onions, green pepper and grated carrots.
Add catsup.
Bake in 325° oven for one hour or until as dry as desired.

title: cabbage goulash
directions: In a large kettle, brown sausage, beef and onion.
Drain off any fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except cabbage; mix well. Stir in cabbage and simmer, 15 to 20 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Serves 8.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Add sugar and water to cherries.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over jello and stir until dissolved.
Place in refrigerator until cool. Remove and add Coke, pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate until set.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: In 5-quart kettle on medium heat, heat oil.
Add onion, celery and garlic; saute for 2 minutes or until tender.
Stir in bouillon cubes, water and tomatoes with liquid, crushing tomatoes into little pieces.
Over high heat, add carrots, cauliflowerets, lima beans, marjoram, thyme and pepper.
Return to boiling, reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes longer.
Add parsley, if desired.

title: party style hot chicken
directions: Combine ingredients; put in greased casserole.
Put in 1 cup potato chips on top.
Cover chips with 1/2 cup grated cheese. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Should be bubbly.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix together until smooth. Dip hot dogs into mix and deep fry. Yields 8 to 10 corn dogs.

title: unleavened communion bread
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, salt and sugar until like coarse cornmeal. Add cold water.
Roll as for pie dough, approximately 1/8-inch thick onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick with a fork.
Cut into bite size pieces (1/4-inch squares) with a knife before baking.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until very light brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar,
water
and cornstarch together.
Bring to a boil, stirring
constantly.
Add	jello
and cool to lukewarm. Pour over berries in pie shell.
Chill.
When ready to serve, top with whipped cream.

title: french onion soup
directions: Fry onions gently
in
fat
until lightly browned.
Add stock, and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: dipsy devil dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vegetables.
Beat until creamy.
Makes about 1 cup.
Use as a vegetable dip.

title: shirley's casserole
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients.
Add all other ingredients and bake.

title: tostadas
directions: Heat oil in small skillet.
Fry corn tortillas, one at a time, in oil until crisp and hard.
Brown ground beef.
Add spices and stir.
Drain meat.
Add refried beans to meat and heat.
Spread over corn tortillas.
Add lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Sour cream and salsa are optional.
Enjoy!!
Quick, easy and inexpensive.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cocoa together.
Add to creamed mixture; mix until blended.
Add chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet until just set, about 6 to 8 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Do not overbake.
They will look a little raw until cool.

title: chipped chopped ham spread
directions: In a big bowl mix all ingredients together, except semi-hard rolls, and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next day cut the rolls in half, on one side smear a little amount of butter and put on spread.
Close the roll with the other half and mount in aluminum foil.
Heat oven to 350°F and bake for 15 to 20 minutes. If you do not use up all the rolls at once, the rest mounted in aluminum foil can be stored in refrigerator for 2 days.

title: christmas salad
directions: Stir pudding in pineapple and juice.
Mix in nuts, marshmallows and cherries. Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Partially thaw vegetables (enough to break apart) and mix with onions, mushrooms and chestnuts.
Place into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and Cheez Whiz.
Heat just enough to be able to mix well.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute tips in butter; add flour and brown.
Add hot beef stock and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Reduce wine and vinegar to 1/2 and add to above.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and roll into 1-inch balls.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients into balls.
Brown in butter at 250° in electric frypan or regular pan on medium high heat.
Melt catsup and currant jelly in frypan.
Simmer meat balls and sauce together for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until frothy.
Gradually beat in oil; add dry ingredients.
Beat at high speed 4 minutes.
Add carrots, zucchini, nuts and currants or raisins.
Pour in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fudge oat cake
directions: Pour water over oats and let stand 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and add cooled oats.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes with apricots
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Cut sweet potatoes into thick slices.
Arrange 1 layer in 10x6x2 greased baking dish.
Cover with layer of apricots sprinkled with some brown sugar.
Repeat layers.
Combine butter,
reserved apricot liquid and orange rind. Pour over layers.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes - basting once or twice with liquid from bottom of dish.
Top with nuts during last 5 minutes.

title: lucy webb's barbecued meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll out between waxed paper sheets to a thickness of 1/4-inch.
Remove top sheet.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups grated Cheddar cheese.
Lift waxed paper and roll like a jelly roll.
Turn ends in to keep cheese inside.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with sauce and bake 15 minutes more.

title: crowd chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; add 2 cups cheese.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream; add to chicken mixture and toss. Spoon into 2 greased 13 x 9-inch baking dishes.
Sprinkle with chips.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.
Serves 24.

title: bread machine buttermilk wheat bread
directions: In bread machine pan, place all ingredients in order given. Select "white bread" setting.
Bake according to bread machine directions.
Makes 1 medium loaf (16 slices).

title: vegetarian spaghetti sauce
directions: Crush garlic and chop onion and brown in oil.
Add canned tomatoes and tomato sauce, mushrooms, salt, chopped squash (optional) and spices.
Bring to boil; simmer for at least 2 hours.
Good for weight watchers.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: sticky chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish. Melt butter; add honey, mustard, salt and curry powder. Pour over chicken and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. This is good, but all chicken is good.

title: sweet sour green beans
directions: Cook beans until crisp and tender (6 to 8 minutes). Drain. Plunge into ice water; drain.
Set aside. Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Keep 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Stir in flour. Cook until bubbly.
Stir in water, vinegar and sugar. Heat to boiling and slightly thickened.
Add beans and toss occasionally. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and bacon.

title: green chili corn bread
directions: Mix meal, eggs, oil and milk.
Add other ingredients and stir. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Bread is done when inserted knife comes out clean.

title: quick mix pepperoni batter bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
Mix together remaining ingredients, including yeast, in a large bowl.
Stir in margarine and water into dry mixture.
Mix in only enough flour to make very thick batter. Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Turn batter into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Let rise in warm draft-free place until double in size, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Check for doneness.
Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and celery in oil.
Cook a few minutes.
Brown meat in Dutch oven.
Add onions, celery, green pepper, tomatoes, puree and seasonings.
Simmer for about an hour. Add mushrooms last 15 minutes.
Set off heat and add 1/2 grated cheese.
Stir.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo until soft.
Add water and bouillon cubes and dissolve.
Add egg noodles and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli, garlic and pepper.
Cook broccoli until it thaws.
Add 6 cups milk and cheese cut in cubes.
Stir until cheese melts, then cook for 30 minutes on low heat.
Do not boil.
Serve with a salad and hot French bread.
Makes a large pot of rich and delicious soup.

title: chinese barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Good on spareribs or chicken.

title: spiced pecans
directions: In a bowl, beat egg white and water until frothy, not stiff. Add pecans and mix until nuts are covered.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in
a small bowl and pour over pecans. Stir well with wooden spoon until pecans are coated.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Put chocolate pieces and milk in a bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on 100% power for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Stir.
Add another 30 seconds if needed.
Stir in almond extract.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Dip with bananas, strawberries, pound cake, pineapple or apples.

title: escalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
Peel and slice into baking dish. Add ham and mushroom soup.
Bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes. Quick and good!

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg, water and raisins in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon juice.
Cool slightly.
Pour into a pie shell.
Cut other crust in criss-cross strips.
Put on top.
Brush melted butter on this and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased baking sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes or until brown. Serves 8 to 10.

title: roast & gravy
directions: Cook roast and spices until tender.
Drain & slice.
Add gravy and onion soup mix.
Simmer 2 hours until done.

title: coffee cake(easy)
directions: Put egg in measuring cup and add milk to make one cup.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add shortening and mix with pastry blender (or two knives) until like cornmeal.
Add egg and milk and put into greased pan.
Sprinkle sugar, nuts or chocolate chips and cinnamon.
Cut dough with knife like you would marble cake.
Add some sugar on top with cinnamon.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, salt and onion.
Layer baking dish with Doritos.
Put meat mixture on top of Doritos.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel and pour mixture over meat.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles. Remove from oven and top with grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with crumbled Doritos.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together in a square baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: opossum pie
directions: Wash opossum inside and out and salt.
Heat lard in roasting pan.
Stir-fry garlic, onions and ginger.
Heat until starts to smoke.
Shake flour over opossum and brown in lard for two minutes.
Place opossum in roasting pan with paws crossed over chest, adding carrots, onions, potatoes and celery.
Add stock and sherry and cook at 325° for 2 hours.
Add peas.
Recover and heat 8 more minutes.
Best served with rice, turnip greens and corn bread.
Serves 8 to 12 or whoever you can get to eat it!

title: scrambled egg bake
directions: In a large mixing bowl with a wire whisk or fork, beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in milk; mix well.
Add cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves immediately.

title: oatmeal apple cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla on medium speed.
Combine flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and salt.
Beat into creamed mixture at low speed until well blended.
Stir in oats. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 13 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet. Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and cocoa and add alternately with buttermilk and flavoring.
Bake in 4 nine-inch greased and floured cake pans at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: piccalilli
directions: Chop tomatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand for 24 hours and drain.
Chop together peppers, and celery and add with sugar and vinegar to tomatoes and onions.
Tie spices in a bag and add to the ingredients; cook slowly until ingredients are tender, about 2 or 3 hours.
Remove the spice bag.
Place piccalilli in sterilized jars and seal.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Soften cream cheese in bowl. Core mushrooms after removing stems.

title: quickie barbecue
directions: Mix corned beef and whatever kind of barbecue sauce you like and heat.
Serve on bun with cole slaw.

title: marshmallow cloud cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Keep marshmallows frozen until ready to use (they thaw quickly).
Combine flour, cocoa and soda.
Set aside.
Combine sugars; blend in butter.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and chocolate chips.
Blend at low speed.
Batter will be stiff.
Gather 4 to 5 frozen marshmallows in your hand.
Cover with heaping teaspoonful of dough.
Wrap marshmallows in dough, making a 2 inch ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn and sausage soup
directions: Slice sausage and brown in heavy soup pot. Add onions and saute until tender. Stir in potatoes, water, salt, basil, pepper and parsley. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Stir in corn and milk. Heat to a boil, but do not boil. Serve with a tossed salad and crusty bread. Makes 8 bowls.

title: judy's pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle more nuts on top.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Pour brandy
and
cider into large coffee pot.	Combine remaining
ingredients
and
pour
into the percolator basket. Perk until done.
Makes 9 to 10 cups of cider.

title: creamy orange glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pour over hot cake.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat soup to dissolve cream cheese in soup.
Soften gelatin in 3/4 cup cold water, then add to soup and stir to dissolve, then cool.
Add peppers, celery, onions and mayonnaise to soup mixture. Add crab meat.
Spray mold with Pam.

title: crazy cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Stir in peanut butter and brown sugar.
Cool slightly and then stir in 3/4 of Cool Whip.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pie.

title: white chili
directions: Drain soaked beans.
Put beans, chicken broth, garlic and half of the onions into a large soup pot.
Bring to a boil; cover, lower heat and simmer until beans are soft, about 3 hours, adding more broth, if necessary.

title: vodka slushes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Let set in freezer for at least 24 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with 7-Up.

title: soft drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Frost or sprinkle with sugar just before you put in oven.

title: chicken roll-ups(old recipe)
directions: Mix chicken with 1 1/4 cups cheese.
Put mixture in center of each roll and "roll up".
Lay rolls in 9 x 13-inch pans.
Heat soup, milk and 3/4 cup cheese until cheese melts.
Pour over rolls. Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 400° in greased muffin pan until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: crab cakes canton
directions: Combine crab meat, bread crumbs, garlic and ginger in bowl. Mix well.
Add egg white and teriyaki sauce; mix well.
Shape into patties, about 1/2-inch thick and 2-inch in diameter.
Heat 1 teaspoon oil into large nonstick skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add crab cakes to hot oil.
Cook 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.

title: easy bake cheese omelet
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Set aside.
Slightly beat egg yolks.
Add 1/2 cup of the Cheddar cheese soup.
Mix well. Fold yolk mixture into white mixture.
Spread in an ungreased 8 1/2-inch round baking dish. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until puffy and golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cut cheese into cubes; place in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water, stirring frequently until melted.
Place sausage, Bisquick and cheese in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
May be frozen before baking.
Place on cookie sheet to freeze until firm, then place in plastic bags or container, then freeze until needed.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain well.
Add dressing as needed to cook pasta.
Add feta cheese, olives, and stir.
Add parmesan and stir. Add tomatoes and broccoli.
Chill and serve.
Top with chopped fresh basil for presentation.

title: minnesota wild rice soup
directions: Brown beef.
Add next nine ingredients and simmer 30 minutes. Add soup and water.
Stir and simmer 30 minutes.
Can be put in crock pot until ready to serve.

title: damson pie
directions: Put all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes, until crust is pretty and brown and pie does not jiggle (firm).
Good with Cool Whip on top.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients and knead 5 minutes.
Roll 1/4-inch.
Cut and place on greased pan.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheesy scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in small amount of water until tender; drain well.
Melt butter over low heat; add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Stir in spices.

title: bean soup
directions: *Lawry's seasoning, Johnny's seasoning, garlic salt, Watkins soup and vegetable seasoning, flavor enhancer.

title: mississippi pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend in about 1/2 of the flour and all baking powder.
Stir in milks and extracts.
Then blend in remaining flour.
Beat a short while until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let sit in Bundt pan 10 minutes, then turn over on cake plate.
When cool,
sprinkle powdered sugar lightly.
Then add fresh fruit to the plate.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Lightly spray 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Line bottom of pan with ladyfinger halves, split sides up.
Cut 10 to 12 additional ladyfinger halves in half.
Use to line side of pan, allowing cut ends to rest on ladyfingers in bottom of pan.
Set aside on baking sheet.

title: liver pate
directions: Saute liver in butter.
Mash and simmer.
Add onion and spices.
Simmer 2 more minutes.
Whip until smooth.
Serve with crackers.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni; mix with all other ingredients. Season to taste.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Add ground cracker crumbs to top and butter dots for a brown top.

title: baked scallop casserole
directions: Place rinsed scallops in a greased casserole dish. Pour milk over scallops and sprinkle with salt, pepper, and lemon juice. Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.
Add Ritz crumbs to melted butter and mix well.
When scallops are finished baking, remove from oven and spread crumb mixture evenly over scallops.
Place under broiler just until golden brown.

title: yum yums
directions: Mix and pat in a 9 x 15-inch pan.

title: mexican casserole corn bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Brown ground meat. Melt cheese with Ro-Tel tomatoes. Layer 1/2 batter, then all of ground meat, all of cheese mixture and chopped onions. Top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter, cocoa and vanilla in pan.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Add oatmeal and coconut.
Using a tablespoon, drop mixture about an inch apart on wax paper.
Let stand until the cookies have hardened.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add bread, pineapple and oranges. In separate bowl, beat eggs and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Set aside; combine oil, eggs and vanilla and add to dry ingredients. Do not overmix.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields about 24 brownies.

title: old fashioned lentil soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until lentils are tender (1/2 hour in pressure cooker).
Take out ham bone.
Strip off bits of meat and return to soup.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with 2 tablespoons vinegar on top.
Croutons may also be served with soup.
Serves 8.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across the grain into thin strips, 1/8-inch thick. Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in large frying pan. Add beef and toss over high heat until browned. If beef is not tender, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are tender. Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to pan.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: texas hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly and pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Serve with salad for complete meal.

title: chiffon pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and pineapple juice until smooth; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add Jell-O, then let cool completely. Whip milk which has been refrigerated overnight.
Add lemon juice. Fold cooled Jell-O mixture into whipped milk, blending well. Place mixture into 2 prepared crusts.
Refrigerate and then serve.

title: castle hamburgers
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Make into patties and fry. Put holes in burgers to cook evenly.

title: manest(poor people's soup)
directions: Wash lettuce in salt water and rinse.
Cut lettuce into 3-inch pieces.
Place in large pot; cover with water.
cut celery into 1-inch pieces and carrots into 1-inch pieces; add to endive.
Add salt to taste.
Cover and cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until tender. Cover saucepan lightly with oil.
Fry garlic lightly.
Add tomato sauce.
Add salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Simmer until it starts to thicken (10 to 15 minutes).
Add beans and simmer about 1/2 hour, until thickened.
Drain vegetables, saving vegetable water.
Add vegetables to bean sauce; slowly add water until thick, but soupy.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain liquid from beets into saucepan.
Boil down to half. Shake together vinegar and flour.
Stir into boiling mixture.
Add sugar and salt; bring to boil.
Add beets and butter; heat through.

title: black bean and rice soup
directions: Place beans with liquid in blender; blend until smooth.
Pour into large saucepan.
Stir in water, oregano and garlic powder and bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with chopped onions if desired.

title: stewed pears
directions: Pare and core pears.
Place in cold water until ready to use. Make syrup.
Add fruit, cored side down.
Boil gently until soft. Add lemon juice before done.

title: cocoa fudge brownies
directions: Heat shortening and cocoa in saucepan until melted.
Stir in sugar and milk; bring to a boil.
Add beaten eggs and all dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Wait 5 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with spoon (no mixer).
Batter will be stiff.
Spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or cream cheese frosting.

title: cranberry oatmeal square
directions: Mix 2nd mixture well and put half into a 7 x 11-inch pan; press firmly.
Pour in cranberry mixture and cool with remaining dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in crushed pineapple and bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in a 9-inch square pan.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cheese fritters
directions: In a medium bowl, beat the cottage cheese and egg together. Stir in the half and half, flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and nutmeg. Mix until just combined. Fill a deep pot to the 2-inch mark with oil. Heat to 375°F (190°C). Drop batter by rounded tablespoonfuls into the hot oil. Fry until golden brown on all sides, about 3 to 4 minutes. Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Serve hot!

title: snack bars
directions: In a very large bowl, combine the first five ingredients.
In a saucepan over low heat, cook and stir marshmallows and butter until marshmallows are melted.
Add honey and mix well.
Pour over cereal mixture; mix well.
Add chips, M&M's or raisins if desired. Pat two-thirds into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and the remaining third into a 9-inch square pan.
Cool.
Yield:
4 to 5 dozen.

title: blueberry streusel cobbler
directions: In bowl, combine berries, sweetened condensed milk and rind. In large bowl, cut 3/4 cup margarine into 1 1/2 cups biscuit mix until crumbly.
Add berry mixture.
Spread in greased 9-inch square baking pan.
In bowl, combine 1/2 cup biscuit mix and sugar; cut in 2 tablespoons margarine until crumbly.
Add nuts. Sprinkle over cobbler.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm with ice cream and Blueberry Sauce.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a well greased 9x13 inch pan.
Bake for about 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup, water and salt.
Bring to a steady boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda.
Stir until thoroughly mixed. (Syrup will be foamy.)
Pour over popped popcorn.
Mix gently. Bake for 1 hour at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour mix onto wax paper or on clean large tea towel separating corn gently. Cool.

title: rice and chicken almondine
directions: Saute almonds and onion in butter for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add bouillon and cream, stirring until thickened.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: grandma brasch's molasses cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in boiling water.
Blend together sugar, shortening and egg.
Add molasses; blend.
Carefully add water. Mix in spices (according to your taste).
Gradually add in flour until a soft dough.
Scoop tablespoon size balls and roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: marbled angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare cake according to package directions.
Measure 4 cups of batter into separate bowl. Gradually, fold cocoa into batter until well blended, be careful not to deflate batter.
Alternately pour vanilla and chocolate batters into ungreased tube pan.
Cut through batter with knife to marble batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, do not underbake.
Invert pan on heatproof funnel or bottle.
Cool for 2 hours.
Run knife along sides to loosen cake, place on platter.
May be eaten plain or drizzled with chocolate glaze.

title: caesar salad
directions: Cut up or tear lettuce.
Oil the bowl with oily dressing; toss lettuce with creamy dressing.
Then add Parmesan cheese.
Toss lettuce with oily dressing, then add Parmesan cheese.
Add croutons just before serving.
Add cucumber and tomato, if desired.

title: cook frosting
directions: Cook until thick the flour and milk.
Cream the butter, granulated sugar and vanilla.
Add both mixtures together and beat for 16 minutes.
Frost cake and refrigerate.

title: poppy seed muffins(makes 1 dozen)
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Make a well in center.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until moist.
Spoon into greased muffin pan, filling 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie 3
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together thoroughly. Add the eggs, syrup and salt.
Mix well.
Add the vanilla and pecans.
Pour into the pie pan lined with pastry. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° until firm.

title: buckaroo beans
directions: Boil beans in 6 cups boiling water for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Rinse twice.
Add 3 1/2 cups fresh water and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 1/2 hours uncovered.
Serves 12.

title: special french toast
directions: Beat eggs and cream together.
Add Triple Sec, granulated sugar, orange zest and cinnamon; whisk until well blended.
Pour into shallow bowl.

title: tapioca
directions: Soak tapioca overnight in water.
Stir in 2 cups whipped topping and some nut meats.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: budget shrimp creole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in oleo.
Remove from heat, stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in shrimp.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: bean and sausage soup
directions: Pick through and rinse beans.
Place in a 4 quart pot and cover with at least 2 inches of water.
Bring to a boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cover, and let stand in the refrigerator overnight. Drain and rinse beans.
Place beans in crockpot with canned tomatoes, broth, wine, and vegetables.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.
In a skillet, cook the sausage over medium heat until done.
Slice links into 1/2 inch pieces.
Add meat to the crockpot and cook another 30 to 60 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma straub's chili sauce
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Mash tomatoes to chunky.
Add all other ingredients to mix.
Cook slowly until thickens, stirring occasionally to prevent burning, about 3 to 4 hours.

title: cabbage surprise
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot.
Cover with water and bring to boil.
Boil 10 minutes, then simmer until soft.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: apple cinnamon baked french toast
directions: Slice bread into 1-inch thick slices.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with oil and arrange bread slices tightly together.
Mix eggs, milk, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Pour half of mixture over bread. Arrange sliced apples on top and pour balance of egg mixture over top.
Take remaining 1/2 cup of sugar and mix it with the cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let rest for 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with hot syrup.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Melt cheese in crock-pot; add sauce and meat and simmer for awhile.
Serve with tortilla chips as dippers.

title: quick cabbage casserole
directions: Slice cabbage, cook 10 minutes in salt water.
Drain.
Mix soup, milk, cabbage and cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring to boil the water and sugar.
Add Jell-O and pie filling. Mix and bring to boil again, then cool slightly and add remaining 4 ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, cinnamon, baking soda, apples and nuts.
Bake 1 hour or more at 350° to 375° in well greased tube pan.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix meat, milk, egg, oatmeal, onion and salt.
Form into balls.
Make sauce out of remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Don't cover.
Add pepper if desired.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix dressing and oil; add seasonings.
Pour over crackers.
Put in warm oven, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: texas-style beans and rice
directions: Combine beans, tomatoes, picante sauce, beer and brown sugar in large saucepan.
Simmer uncovered 20 minutes.
Stir in rice and salt; heat through.
Sprinkle with onion and cilantro.

title: white cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese and put in a saucepan. Over medium - low heat, add just enough milk to melt the cheese to the desired consistency, stirring constantly so cheese doesn't burn. Blend in finely chopped jalapenos to taste. Leftovers may be refrigerated and reheated on the stovetop by adding a little milk and stirring over medium - low heat.

title: amaretto
directions: Bring brown sugar and water to a boil.
Let syrup cool.
Mix almond extract and vodka to syrup.
Shake well.
Let stand for 3 days.

title: christmas candy
directions: With hands thoroughly mix above ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Place on wax paper and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: vidalia onion seafood casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in margarine.
Add pimento, cream of celery soup, milk and cream cheese.
Heat slowly until blended.
Add rice and shrimp; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place crushed crackers on top the last 10 minutes of baking.
(Cover top of casserole with crumbs.)

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground meat; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans and seasoning.
Prepare muffin mix according to the package directions.
Spread muffin mix batter over chili mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: grandma stoddard's peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir sugar, oleo and milk together in pan.
Boil to soft ball stage (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased pan.
Allow 30 minutes to cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Put crushed cornflakes on top after baking with dots of butter.
Place back in oven for a few minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix until crumbs in a bowl.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar in a bowl.
Blend in vanilla and sour cream.
Chill about 30 minutes.

title: green beans and corn casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish; combine butter and cracker crumbs and press one-half of mixture into the bottom of the casserole dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in dish twice; top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: salted pecans
directions: Coat pecans with melted margarine; sprinkle with salt.
Bake 20 minutes at 275°.
Cool on paper towels.

title: beef cheese log
directions: Soften cream cheese. In a large bowl, add mayo and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well. Add olives, parsley and onion. Chill until firm. On wax paper, shape into a 1 1/2-inch roll. Roll in dried beef. Garnish with parsley. Serve with crackers.

directions: Brown
