title: party fizz
directions: Pour the orange juice into a bowl, then the pineapple juice and club soda.
Add the sherbet and mix everything with an egg beater.
Pour the fizz into glasses.

title: pot roast
directions: Dredge roast in flour.
Brown slowly on all sides in hot fat. Season generously with salt and pepper.
Add onions.
Mix remaining ingredients except mushrooms and add to roast.
Cover and cook slowly at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Then add mushrooms. Blend 2 tablespoons flour to thicken gravy.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine, brown sugar and pretzels.
Mix well and pat into a lightly buttered 9 x 12-inch Pyrex baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
While hot, add strawberries.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken.

title: peanut butter health bread
directions: In medium bowl, stir flour, oats, baking powder, and salt.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat peanut butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add milk.
With mixer on low, beat in dry ingredients until smooth.
Stir in raisins.

title: country sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil and pat mixture into 8 small cakes.
Heat oil in large skillet and fry cakes about 20 minutes, turning until brown and crisp on both sides.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 375°.
The last 15 minutes of baking, add crushed potato chips on top.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: In an electric skillet, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Set the heat control at 280°.
Bring to full boil and boil for 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cocoa, flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Add egg yolks, butter and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Within an hour of serving, spread whipped cream over top.

title: gooey buns
directions: Grind bologna and cheese. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Butter 6 buns. Fill and wrap individually in tinfoil. Bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Using your favorite casserole dish layer stuffing, asparagus and eggs and sprinkle with pepper and onion.
Repeat until dish is full.
Pour soup and asparagus liquid on top and spread.
Bake at 350° until bubbles up.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, margarine, milk and vanilla and pour into casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, pecans and margarine in a medium bowl and sprinkle over potatoes mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Combine cornstarch and water in a small saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Serve warm as a dip with fresh fruit.
Serves 1 cup.

title: wayne's hush puppies(for large gatherings)
directions: Mix all ingredients well; drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Submerge, if possible, until brown.
Enjoy!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Knead, if necessary.
Make into walnut size balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: beginner's pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt together in bowl.
Cut in shortening with fork until mixture looks like corn meal.
Add water a little at a time.
Let set a few minutes.
Knead on floured surface and shape into pie shell.

title: spinach polenta casserole
directions: Saute garlic in oil until crisp.
Remove and add the spinach and salt and pepper to taste.
Steam until limp.
Remove from pan and squeeze dry when cool.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix together 1 hour over low heat until thick.
When thick, remove from heat.
Add 4 scoops vanilla ice cream and vanilla extract.
Stir.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Enjoy!

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Slowly add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk.
Add flour and vanilla and mix well.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Gently press a cherry half or pecan half into each cookie.
Bake at 350° until bottom of cookies start to brown, 6 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Place all ingredients in cooker.
Bring to a boil; turn down. When it forms a soft ball in cold water, take off stove.
Let cool, then mix with a mixer.

title: church windows candies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Let cool slightly.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Spread coconut on wax paper.
Divide mixture into four rolls.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap in wax paper. Place in refrigerator for 24 hours before slicing.
Cut in 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: corn custard
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in eggs.
Scald milk and 2 tablespoons butter; add to corn mixture.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Mix crumbs in 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake until browned.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; add to other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with grated cheese, if desired.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: aunt jo's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix and boil sugar, brown sugar, salt and milk for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and beat thoroughly. Immediately place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Beat eggs, brown sugar, oil and vanilla until thick and foamy. Stir in rhubarb and nuts.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices.
Add to the rhubarb mixture and stir until just blended.

title: hungarian rhapsody
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large skillet.
Over high heat, brown the cutlets briefly on both sides; do not overcook.
Reserve browned cutlets on a warmed platter.
In the same skillet over medium heat, saute chopped onion and garlic in the remaining olive oil until lightly browned, 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir in paprika and cook 2 minutes longer.
Blend in sour cream until just heated through.
Do not allow the mixture to boil!
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from
heat.
Spoon the sauce over the cutlets; serve with boiled rice.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Heat the oven to 325°.
Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream by hand.
Pour 1/2 of batter in cake pan (greased and floured). Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Swirl.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Ice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Generously grease bottoms only of 2 baking pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches. Beat all ingredients on low speed, scraping bowl constantly for 1 minute.
Beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted into center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pans. Cool completely before slicing.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine first 5 dry ingredients.
Add milk, vanilla and butter and beat until smooth.
Stir in the walnuts and spread the batter in a buttered 6 cup casserole.
Over the batter, sprinkle the mixture of the brown sugar and cocoa.
Over this, pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Do not attempt to turn out this cake.
The bottom is full of fudge sauce.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: christmas punch(ison family tradition)
directions: You will need a punch bowl, cups, potato masher and whisk.

title: microwave taco chops
directions: Combine taco mix with cornflake crumbs.
Dip one side of each chop into egg and then into crumb mixture.
Reserve remaining egg and crumbs.
Place crumb side up into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or large pie plate, placing meaty ends of chops toward outside of dish.
Microwave uncovered on High for 5 minutes, turning dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes.
Turn chops over; top with remaining egg and crumbs.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water on High for 30 seconds. Stir.
Pour around (not over) chops.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave for 6 minutes on High, rotating dish once.
Let stand covered for 5 minutes.
Use pan drippings for gravy, if desired. Serves 4.
Simply delicious!

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Beat all together with mixer.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: spiced sesame seed crescents
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, mace and salt. Gradually stir sugar into softened butter. Beat in egg. Add flour mixture gradually, mixing after each addition. Let dough stand 30 minutes at room temperature. With fingers, on waxed paper, shape a rounded teaspoonful of dough at a time into a roll 2-inches long. Taper ends. Roll in lightly toasted sesame seed. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Curve ends to form crescents. Bake in a 375° oven 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned around the bottom. Cool on wire rack.

title: quick fruit pie
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Fill with fruit and seal edges like fried pies.
Place in single layer in casserole dish.
Pour liquid mixture over pies.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: You will also need measuring cups and spoons, a bowl, an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan and an oven.
Preheat oven to 350°, then smear the inside of the pan with shortening.

title: italian chicken
directions: Soak chicken pieces in beaten eggs overnight.
Roll chicken pieces in Italian bread crumbs and saute in butter.
Arrange pieces in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add to the drippings in your frying pan, 1 cup chicken broth and 1/2 cup dry white wine.
Pour over chicken; top with mushrooms and grated Muenster cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (decrease oven temperature to 325° if using a glass baking dish).

title: easy pie crust
directions: Put all ingredients in pie plate.
Mix well and press into shape, partially covering rim of plate.
Pinch dough into fluting for edge. Prick bottom and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: banana burrito
directions: Lay tortilla on flat surface; spread evenly with peanut butter and raspberry spread.
Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.
Place banana on edge of tortilla; roll up to enclose.
Wrap loosely in paper towel.
Microwave on High for 35 seconds.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix together ice cream and Cool Whip.
Smooth in bowl.
Freeze slightly until it mounds, then spoon into graham cracker crust. Freeze for 4 hours.

title: no salt herb shaker
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into salt shaker and use instead of salt.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla in a 1-quart glass dish.
Cut butter in slices and put on top.
Cook on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into wax paper lined 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: football popcorn
directions: Melt oleo in a saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar.
Simmer until syrup forms.
Immediately pour over already popped popcorn.
Stir well.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Ham can be substituted for sausage.

title: plain jane cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar together until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, until they are mixed in well.
Gradually add milk and flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: croquettes
directions: Stir onion in melted butter until brown.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add water and stir until thick.
Add meat and cook 2 minutes.
Break in egg.
Stir until mixed.
Chill.
To mold, dip in cracker meal, seasoned beaten eggs, then cracker meal again. Chill.
Roll in melted butter; cook on baking sheet at 350°
for one-half hour.
Serve with tomato or mushroom sauce.
Makes 6 regular size.

title: nadine krall's pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in frypan.
Pour onion soup mix and enough water over chops to keep chops covered.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add Minute rice and simmer.
For two people, use 1/2 cup rice.

title: honey buttermilk rolls
directions: Place all ingredients into bread machine pan in the order listed. Use "dough" setting to make dough. Remove when dough setting is done. Use margarine to coat hands for easy removal and roll shaping.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Blend Eagle Brand, Cool Whip, lemon juice, crushed pineapple, cherry jello and almond flavoring. Add bananas, cherry pie filling and pecans. Fold in. Chill.

title: creamy reception punch
directions: Spoon vanilla ice cream by tablespoons into a large punch bowl. Add juices, stirring to muddle ice cream.
Slowly pour in 7-Up or Sprite. Stir to mix.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Bake for 30 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake on ungreased griddle.
Pour batter from 1/4 cup measuring cup.
Makes 12 small cakes.

title: "green stuff" salad
directions: Heat pear juice to boiling.
Pour over jello and dissolve. While hot, pour jello over cream cheese.
Mix well with mixer until blended.
Place mixture in refrigerator or freezer until it starts to set.
Add whipped cream with mixer until well blended. Add nuts and pears; pour into serving bowl.
Chill until firm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
May freeze if wanted.

title: confectioners sugar
directions: Whirl together in blender until fine.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: In large saucepan combine ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve warm.

title: peppers 'n potatoes
directions: In 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat margarine until bubbly; add bell peppers, onions and garlic.
Saute until vegetables are softened.
Stir in water, broth mix and pepper; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Add potatoes, cover and let simmer, stirring occasionally, until tender.
(Add more water if necessary to prevent sticking.)

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together in order given.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully, they brown quickly.
You can make these any size you like.

title: corn salad with mesquite turkey breast
directions: Toss together corn, celery, bell pepper, olives and cilantro in large bowl. Combine dressing and cumin in measuring cup and pour over corn mixture. Toss to coat. Line 4 plates with spinach leaves and place 1 cup corn salad in center of each plate. Fold 4 to 5 slices turkey into fourths and tuck around corn salad or cut turkey into strips and arrange strips around corn.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: This dip is put in layers; either on a glass plate or in a glass bowl.

title: supreme chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Chop in bite-size pieces.
Slice water chestnuts.
Crush crackers.
Sprinkle 1/2 crackers in bottom of baking dish.
Mix chicken soup, water chestnuts, sour cream and onions together.
Pour in baking dish.
Top with remaining crumbs and sprinkle butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Cook and stir beef and onions until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix; spread into plate.
Top with chillies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds, in blender or 1 minute with mixer.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with sliced tomatoes and cheese, then bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes or longer.
Cool 5 minutes. Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes, shredded lettuce and Cheddar cheese.

title: diabetic's fruit salad
directions: Mix juice from pineapple, lemon juice and enough orange juice to make 1 cup.
Add sweetener.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to juice.
Boil and stir until thick.
Cool.
Combine canned fruit and fresh fruit.
Mix in fruit dressing; allow to stand to let flavors blend.
Makes 1 cup dressing.
Leftover will keep or double recipe.

title: pineapple shortcake
directions: Just dip canned biscuits in vegetable oil. Turn in granulated sugar and place on cookie sheet. Flatten each with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake 10 minutes in preheated 425° oven, then on with the golden crushed pineapple and a topping of whipped cream. Garnish with a cherry.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Cook sausage and drain well.
Mix flour, corn meal, egg, milk and oil.
Add sausage.
Place in greased muffin pan and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mustard potato salad
directions: Cool potatoes completely. To make mustard dressing, in a large serving bowl, combine white wine vinegar, Dijon mustard and salt. Whisk in olive oil until well blended.
Add sliced red potatoes, scallions and roasted red peppers.
Toss to coat well with mustard-oil dressing.

title: caramel-peanut pie
directions: Place
cup
sugar in heavy skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and forms a light brown syrup.
Reduce heat to low;
gradually add boiling water in
a slow
stream,
stirring
constantly
with a wire whisk. Remove from heat.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach - mix all ingredients - Serve immediately.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix ingredients; beat well.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven.
Cake is done when it falls in middle.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Allow to melt gradually over low heat.
Stir until creamy.
Add food coloring; mix good.
Add corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Press hole in middle to form a wreath shape.
Press cinnamon candy on to appear as berries.
Allow to harden.
Place layers of wax paper between layers of wreath.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour melted butter over and stir.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Drop by 1/4 teaspoon onto aluminum foil on cookie sheet, leaving lots of room in between.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Let cookies cool on foil before peeling off. Use new foil for each sheet of cookies.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: good homemade ice cream
directions: Beat sugar, Pet milk and egg yolks until sugar is dissolved. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in with vanilla.
Pour in freezer.
If not enough to fill to line, fill with milk.
Any fruit you desire can be added to this.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until done and drain. Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes or until set at 350°.

title: homemade white bread
directions: Heat 4 cups water to 110°; use 3/4 cup of the water and dissolve yeast and 3/4 teaspoon regular sugar.
Stir in flour, Sweet 'N Low, salt, pepper and Crisco.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Microwave until melted. Serve with corn chips.

title: bacon-n-eggs
directions: Cut hard-boiled eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mix with mayonnaise, salt, pepper and crumbled bacon.
Put mixture back into eggs and serve.
Kids love them.
Serve for breakfast with toast.

title: sarah's lasagne
directions: In large heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil. Drain.
Add tomatoes (put through blender), paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes.

title: new england blueberry muffins
directions: Beat together the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients and beat for 1 minute.
Fold in blueberries.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except the pie shell.
Pour into shell and bake at 350° until set, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
In margarine, saute chopped onion, chopped celery and leaves.
Add salt, pepper, sage, thyme (may be omitted and recipe is still just as good) and poultry seasoning.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in small amount of salt water until tender, but crisp.
Drain; add remaining ingredients except crumbs.
Put in shallow 2-quart dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked fish
directions: Dip fish in dressing.
Melt margarine in flat pan.
Pour part off to be used later.
Roll fish in cracker crumbs and put single layer in pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and then chopped onion. Pour remaining margarine over fish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. (May be placed under broiler very briefly after baked for a crisper coating.)

title: holiday sweet potato surprise
directions: Cook the sweet potatoes in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool.
Peel the potatoes and mash. Combine mashed sweet potatoes, frosting, vanilla and cinnamon; mix well. Spoon into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 18 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows. Continue baking 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: carved watermelon
directions: Mix all ingredients until sugar is dissolved.

title: sauce for ribs or burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
The sauce can then be sealed in a jar and stored in the refrigerator or used at once.
Yield:
Enough sauce for three chickens, halved, or for 5 to 6 pounds of ribs.

title: chicken and biscuit dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut each biscuit into half.
In saucepan, put chicken or turkey, gravy, beans, seasoning and pepper.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
This can be baked in a casserole or individual baking cups.
Spoon into dishes and top with three biscuit pieces on each casserole.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until biscuits are golden.
This is a fun recipe for kids to do.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Sift flour, measure, add salt and sift again.
Cream butter, gradually add confectioners sugar and beat until light.
Combine dry ingredients and creamed mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Put dough in 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares before completely cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until comes to boil.
Pour in bowl; cool mixture by putting bowl in cold water with ice cubes in it.
Stir while cooling until thickens. Add 1 1/2 cups whipped cream or Dream Whip.
Mix well.
Pour in 9-inch cold pie shell.
Refrigerate about 2 hours before serving. Serve with more Cool Whip or strawberries.

title: diabetic maple flavored pancake syrup
directions: In small saucepan, combine apple juice and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in butter, Equal, maple flavoring and vanilla.
Serve over pancakes, waffles or French toast.
Makes 1 cup.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix grape jelly and chili sauce.
Warm in microwave.
Place meatballs in crock-pot.
Pour jelly sauce mix over meatballs. Simmer on low for 1 hour or until heated through.

title: rum balls
directions: Sift cocoa and powdered sugar into bowl.
Stir in liquor which has been combined with syrup; mix well.
Add vanilla wafers and nuts; mix well.
Form into 3/4-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Dry several hours.
Freezes well.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: tea tarts
directions: Soak yeast in water until dissolved.
Mix dry ingredients and shortening as for pie crust.
Combine everything as for pie crust. Combine everything just until blended and chill for several hours or overnight.
Roll on sugared board 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in squares.
Put spoon of jam on center of square and fold three cornered.
Press edges together.
Place on pans and let raise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corinne's famous pea salad
directions: Place 1/2 head of lettuce on bottom of bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Layer eggs atop lettuce in bowl.
Add more salt.
Layer as follows:
Peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and Swiss cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add ham and a slice of cheese to breast and fold over.
Secure with long toothpicks.
Coat with flour.
In a large skillet, add 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook about 4 minutes on each side.
Melt remaining butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion; saute.
Add water, chicken bouillon, parsley, and chives.
Bring to a boil. Return chicken to sauce.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Bring sauce to boil again and stir in heavy cream.
Cook on low heat until sauce thickens slightly.
Pour sauce over chicken to serve.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Cook cake according to directions on package.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put glaze on top of cake (cooled).
Place cut strawberries on top and top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Cook, covered, for about 1 hour at 250° in a 2-quart casserole.
May add ripened bananas.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: sunflower seed cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and eggs. Add water and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes about 120.

title: sausage-peach breakfast bake
directions: Drain peaches and reserve liquid.
Cut sausage links crosswise into bite-size pieces.
Prepare pancake mix as usual, except use up to 1 c. of peach liquid as part of the mixture.
Turn into a 9 x 13 baking dish and arrange peaches and sausage on top.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with syrup.

title: spiders
directions: Melt chips and then add peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Chill.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust; sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs together with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: *Put small amount into blender until it turns to powder. Measure first, then blend.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet.
Add onions and green pepper; saute.
Add other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix buttermilk baking mix, milk, sugar and eggs together and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange apple slices evenly over the top.
Drizzle apples with melted butter.
Stir sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over all.
Drizzle with cream.
Bake in preheated 350°
oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Wonderful served still warm.
Scoop out with a large spoon to serve.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash and core apples.
Pare apples 1/3 of the way down or slit the skin around the apple about halfway down.
Place apples in baking dish.
Put sugar and butter in center of each apple. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour water around apples to prevent sticking.

title: josette's lasagna roll-ups
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and set aside.
Boil noodles until cooked and rinse with water.	Blend cheeses together and set aside.
Add browned ground meat with sauce and seasoning in a pan and simmer.
Spread cheeses onto noodle on one side.
Roll noodles, curly side out.
Cut in half.
Do so with remainder of noodles.
Pour sauce into baking dish and place noodles with non-curly side down into sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: anytime dip
directions: Low-fat sour cream and mayonnaise may be used.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in jar.
Use 1/3 cup mixture to 1 cup boiling water.
Delicious!!

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble bread together in a pan and bake at 300° until dry and golden brown.
Stir often.
Once dry, add butter, eggs, baking powder, salt, pepper, celery and onion.
Add sage to taste.
Add hot broth and mix well.
Bake in greased pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Crumble brown sugar, butter and flour together like pie dough. Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Mix together by hand the beaten eggs and sour cream.
Mix soda, salt and vanilla with flour mixture. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crumble on reserved topping. Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.
Check at 35 minutes.

title: pudding fruit salad
directions: Drain juices from pineapple and mandarin oranges into large bowl.
Add instant pudding and Tang.
Stir until smooth.
Add bananas, kiwi fruit, pineapple, oranges, grapes and strawberries. Mix well and chill.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
in water and cool until partially set. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 5-cup mold and chill until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Combine beef, salt, pepper, egg and cream.
Shape into 1/4-inch balls.
In skillet, brown meatballs in butter, turning carefully to avoid piercing.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to brown meatballs.
Cover; reduce temperature and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 4 or 5 dozen.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish in microwave. In separate container, mix together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and milk. Pour this mixture over melted butter in casserole dish. Heat berries through. Pour over mixture. Bake at 350°.

title: pasta with chicken
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add chicken, onion and garlic; cook until chicken and onion are tender.

Stir in spaghetti sauce. Reduce heat; simmer, covered, stirring frequently, 10 minutes. Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Serve sauce over hot pasta; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour, salt and milk in top of double boiler.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Add a little of the mixture to egg yolks.
Then add to mixture and cook about 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heap sliced apples in pie plate; add lemon juice and sugar. Add cinnamon as desired.
Crumble brown sugar, butter, flour and salt on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburg noodle casserole
directions: Brown
ground beef.
Cook noodles until not quite done; drain. Put
in
greased casserole.
Put 1 layer hamburg and 1 layer noodles.
Cover
with mushroom soup.
Repeat layers and cover with
celery
soup.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly and lightly browned on top.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients. Blend into first mixture.
Add carrots and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 (10-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: grape sunshine
directions: Using real ripe grapes, wash and remove stems.
Place in large kettle with enough water to cover bottom of pan only. Kettle can be pretty full of grapes.
Cook over medium heat until skins pop open.
Run grapes, skins and seeds through a sieve, crushing grapes and skins as much as possible.
Stir in 1 box of Sure-Jell with pulp in kettle.
Bring to a full boil over high heat.
Add sugar at once, bringing to a full boil again; stir constantly.
Boil 1 minute, then remove from heat.
Skim off foam. Put hot mixture in jars or glasses and top with melted paraffin.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Place chocolate chips on top before baking.
Bake in cake pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: passover rolls or muffins
directions: Boil water and oil together.
Add matzoh meal, sugar and salt. Mix off of the heat.
Beat very well.
Add eggs, 2 at a time, beating very well.
Bake in muffin tin at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-Os in hot water.
Mix together and when thickened, pour over mixture.

title: pizzacato pizza casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Take sausage out of casing and crumble.
Brown and drain off grease.
Stir in tomato puree, sauce, water, mushrooms and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni and stir well.
Put 1/3 of meat and macaroni mixture into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/3 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with remaining 2/3.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in deep Dutch oven pan. Cook until soft. (Boil at 232°.) Add pecans and stir until coated. Spread and separate with fork; cool completely. Store in tin box.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease large casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Lay out on bottom of dish.
Press together.
Cook sausage and drain.
Pour over rolls.
Beat eggs and add milk together. Pour over sausage.
Mix grated cheese.
Pour over top.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: glazed sweet potato pie
directions: Put butter or oleo in hot mashed potatoes; stir until butter is melted.
Add sugar, slightly beaten egg and flavoring.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch crust.
Sprinkle 1/4 sugar over top of pie.
Wait until sugar becomes moist, then put into oven.
Bake at 350° until done and glaze has formed.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; then mix with applesauce.
Add sifted dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Beat and pour into buttered, floured loaf pan.
Bake slowly 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: holiday bourbon slush
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Sprite) and freeze 2 days.

title: italian cookies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat.
Add melted shortening and juice.
Mix well.
Add salt, baking powder, flour and mix until smooth and easy to handle.
Make into different shapes. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Decorate with colored sugar or frosting.

title: barbecue
directions: Place meat in heavy kettle or skillet and cook slowly until meat changes color.
Add onions and cook for 10 to 15 minutes. Add other ingredients, except soup.
Simmer for about 1 hour.
Add soup and cook a while longer.
Salt to taste.

title: apple crisp
directions: Melt the butter; pour over the dry ingredients.
Mix until crumbly.
Spread over 1 can of apple pie filling.
Bake until brown at 325°.

title: pudding bars
directions: Mix instant pudding according to directions. Add cake mix, then bag of chocolate chips. Mix well. Pour on cookie sheet (greased) and bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over chopped apples; let set 10 minutes.
Mix eggs and shortening.
Add dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Stir in apple mixture.
Batter is stiff.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan at 375° for 50 minutes.
Needs no frosting.
Cool before cutting.

title: butterscotch cream cheese bars
directions: In saucepan, melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press half of mixture firmly into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: long island iced tea
directions: Mix together to make 1 serving. Multiply times 4 to make a pitcher.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put tomato paste in large cooking pot.
Add 5 cans warm water and bring to a boil.
Add sugar, oregano, Lawry's salt, onion and Italian seasoning.
Simmer for about 2 hours.
Add mushrooms and browned hamburger during last half hour.
Serve with pasta.
Makes great lasagna too.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: april's beef stew
directions: In a large saucepan, brown meat and drain well.
Return meat to saucepan.
Add onion, garlic and thyme.
Stir in vegetable juice, bouillon and water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.
Stir in potatoes, celery and carrots.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes more.

title: melba sauce
directions: Put frozen raspberries into a quart glass measuring pitcher. Heat, uncovered, in microwave oven 1 minute on High.
Stir to break berries apart. Cook, uncovered, 30 seconds on High or until berries are defrosted.
Stir a mixture of sugar and cornstarch into raspberries, then stir in currant jelly. Cook in microwave oven 6 minutes on High until sauce thickens.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cheese, then mix in Cool Whip and peanut butter.
Pour in graham cracker crust and chill for 1 hour.

title: polo star candy
directions: Melt the almond bark and peanut butter. Remove from heat. Stir in peanuts, rice krispies and marshmallows. Stir until well coated and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in a baking dish.
In a separate bowl, mix honey, mustard, lemon juice and salt.
Spoon half of mixture over chicken.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and congeal.

title: oreo cookie cheesecake
directions: In a food processor, whirl 1/2 package of the cookies, including filling, until they form fine crumbs; mix in butter. Scoop crumbs into a 9-inch cheesecake pan with removable bottom and press crumbs evenly over bottom of pan and about 1/2-inch up sides. Chill crust to firm, about 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water 6 minutes. Drain and rinse well to remove starch.
Set aside.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello	in
hot water.	Add pineapple and blueberries. Chill until firm.

title: dee's strawberry pudding cake
directions: Crumble cake in baking pan.
Put berries over cake.
Let set in freezer while you mix pudding and milk.
Pour mix over cake.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: coconut pecan brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine brownie mix, water, oil and egg.
Beat 50 strokes by hand.
Add frosting and sour cream; mix well.
Spread batter in greased pan.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 42 to 52 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine caramels, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and 1/4 cup margarine in a double boiler until melted.
Combine cake mix, 1/2 cup margarine, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and 1 cup walnuts.
Spread half in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread caramel mixture over the chips.
Top with remaining cake mix.
Bake 18 minutes at 350°.
Do not bake longer!
Cut into bars.

title: hot maple toddy
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients (except optional). Over low heat, simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Serve hot with butter and cinnamon sticks, if desired.

title: poppy seed bread or muffins
directions: Beat all ingredients together in large mixing bowl for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 15 slices per loaf.
(Also, can use for muffins.)
Contains less than 1 gram of fat per 1/2-inch slice.

title: mauna loa muffins(third place winner of 1992 mauna loa contest)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin
tins
with cooking spray. In
large
bowl,	beat milk, oil and
egg.
Blend
in remaining ingredients until flour is just
moistened.
Fill in muffin cups 3/4 full;
sprinkle with sugar.
Bake
until
tops are browned, for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: eggless spice cake
directions: Sift all
ingredients.
Place
in
bowl and add 1/2 cup melted shortening,
cups water and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well and bake
in
layers in a moderate oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: spicy glazed wieners
directions: Cut 3 thin gashes on each wiener.
In medium saucepan over medium heat, cook remaining ingredients, stirring, until cranberry sauce melts and becomes smooth.
Add wieners and heat through. Serve hot with cocktail picks.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: chocolate ice cream (frosty)
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip, then chocolate milk.
Put into electric freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: gumbo
directions: Get
a
large
pot
and
put
in the spareribs, beef and chicken
wings.
Boil
spareribs
for
about 1/2 hour.
Saute 1 pound
of boneless chuck beef and put in large pot.
Saute pack of chicken
wings
and put in pot.
Put in can of tomato puree and tomato
sauce.
Add
diced
onions, salt, pepper, mustard, ketchup, sugar, Adobo seasoning and whole tomatoes.
Simmer for 2 hours and then add 1 pound of deveined shrimp.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Skin chicken breasts and arrange in baking dish.
Place 1 piece of Swiss cheese in each piece of chicken.
Stir together soup and wine or water.
Spoon over chicken.
Top with stuffing mix and drizzle melted butter over each piece of chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 55 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper. Stir in beans and 1/2 can fried onions. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Stir, then top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: watergate salad
directions: *Save some nuts and cherries for top.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh fruit.

title: molded lemon dessert
directions: Make jello according to directions.
When fairly thick, whip the milk.
Add to jello (using large bowl).
Add sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Put 1/2 of crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add jello mixture.
Put remainder of crumbs on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pasta with broccoli di rape and sausage
directions: Remove the long stems and tough outer leaves from the Broccoli di Rape.
Keep florets and small leaves, cut up, place in colander and wash several times.
Pour oil into pan on medium heat.
Lightly crush garlic, place in heated oil and allow to turn golden, then remove garlic if you wish.
Remove casing from sausage, place meat in pan and cook thoroughly, breaking the pieces of meat apart as they continue to cook.
If you still have not removed the garlic, do so now.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon oil from pan; add Broccoli di Rape to pan and mix with cooked sausage.
Keep mixing together, add your broth, mix and cook for approximately 5 minutes.
Mix flour and butter together to form a roux and stir into your mixture.
Cook approximately 5 minutes more until sauce thickens. Serve over pasta and add the grated Italian cheese of choice.

title: sausage and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage. In a large casserole dish, slice potatoes and onion (in rings). Put cheese 1 cup on top of potatoes and onion. Layer browned meat on top of potatoes, onion and cheese. Then put a can of green beans, drained.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake until golden brown.

title: three layer pie
directions: Combine ingredients and bake
in
a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: pineapple whip salad
directions: In large bowl, mix pineapple and sugar.
In saucepan, bring water and gelatin to a boil.
Pour over sugar and pineapple and stir.
Refrigerate until slightly set.
Add carrots, celery, cottage cheese, nuts, whipped topping and mayonnaise to pineapple mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Saute onion and green pepper until transparent.
Add both cans of tomato, then remaining ingredients.
Stir and simmer 30 minutes.

title: healthy sloppy joes
directions: Brown sirloin with onion.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes or so.
Serve open-faced on bread of choice.

title: virgin island soup
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients together 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 more minutes.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Drain chilies and olives.
In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread mixture onto tortillas and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Cover with damp paper towel and plastic wrap to prevent drying out.
Chill for several hours.
To serve, slice tortillas into 1-inch segments.
Serve with salsa for dipping.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco and flour together.
Mix in salt.
Gently mix in ice water with hands.
Roll out for pie.

title: florentine lasagna roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Cool in large bowl of cold water; set aside.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.

title: great pheasant or partridge
directions: Do not thicken!
Pour over meat and bake for 2 hours on low. Serve with rice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Do not use electric mixer.
Use hand wire whisk.
Slightly beat egg yolks; stir in 1 cup milk.
Then stir in remaining milk, sugar and coconut.
Beat egg whites and stir in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until centers jell.
